obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (14503)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 21st January, 1958, vide notification No. 269, dated 21st January 1958, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14503&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Copyright Act, 1957.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (14504)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14504&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) adaptation means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a dramatic work, the conversion of the work into a non-dramatic work;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a literary work or an artistic work, the conversion of the work into a`
  line `dramatic work by way of performance in public or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to a literary or dramatic work, any abridgement of the work or any version of`
  line `the work in which the story or action is conveyed wholly or mainly by means of pictures in a`
  line `form suitable for reproduction in a book, or in a newspaper, magazine or similar periodical; ^1***`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to a musical work, any arrangement or transcription of the work; ^2[and]`
  line
  line `^2[(v) in relation to any work, any use of such work involving its re-arrangement or`
  line alteration;]
  line
  line ^3*****
  line
  line `(b) ^4[work of architecture] means any building or structure having an artistic character or design,`
  line `or any model for such building or structure;`
  line
  line `(c) artistic work means,--`
  line
  line `(i) a painting, a sculpture, a drawing (including a diagram, map, chart or plan), an engraving`
  line `or a photograph, whether or not any such work possesses artistic quality;`
  line
  line `(ii) an ^4[work of architectural]; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any other work of artistic craftsmanship;`
  line
  line `(d) author means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to literary or dramatic work, the author of the work;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a musical work, the composer;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to an artistic work other than a photograph, the artist;`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to a photograph, the person taking the photograph;`
  line
  line `^5[(v) in relation to a cinematograph film or sound recording, the producer; and`
  line
  line `(vi) in relation to any literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work which is`
  line `computer-generated, the person who causes the work to be created;]`
  line
  line `^6[(dd) broadcast means communication to the public--`
  line
  line `(i) by any means of wireless diffusion, whether in any one or more of the forms of signs,`
  line `sounds or visual images; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by wire,`
  line
  line `and includes a re-broadcast;]`
  line
  line `(e) calendar year means the year commencing on the 1st day of January;`
  line
  line `^7[(f) cinematograph film means any work of visual recording ^8*** and includes a sound`
  line `recording accompanying such visual recording and cinematograph shall be construed as including`
  line `any work produced by any process analogous to cinematography including video films;]`
  line
  line `^9 [(fa) commercial rental does not include the rental, lease or lending of a lawfully acquired`
  line `copy of a computer programme, sound recording, visual recording or cinematograph film for`
  line `non-profit purposes by a non-profit library or non-profit educational institution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, a non-profit library or non-profit educational institution means a library or educational institution which receives grants from the Government or exempted from payment of tax under the Income-tax Act, 1961(43 of 1961).]`
  line
  line `^10[(ff) communication to the public means making any work or performance available for being`
  line `seen or heard or otherwise enjoyed by the public directly or by any means of display or diffusion`
  line `other than by issuing physical copies of it, whether a simultaneously or at places and times chosen`
  line `individually, regardless of whether any member of the public actually sees, hears or otherwise enjoys`
  line `the work or performance so made available.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, communication through satellite or cable or any other means of simultaneous communication to more than one household or place of residence`
  line `including residential rooms of any hotel or hostel shall be deemed to be communication to the`
  line public;]
  line
  line `(g) delivery, in relation to a lecture, includes delivery by means of any mechanical instrument`
  line `or by ^11[broadcast];`
  line
  line `(h) dramatic work includes any piece for recitation, choreographic work or entertainment in`
  line `dumb show, the scenic arrangement or acting, form of which is fixed in writing or otherwise but does not include a cinematograph film;`
  line
  line `^12 [(hh) duplicating equipment means any mechanical contrivance or device used or intended to`
  line `be used for making copies of any work;]`
  line
  line `(i) engravings include etchings, lithographs, wood-cuts, prints and other similar works, not`
  line `being photographs;`
  line
  line `(j) exclusive licence means a licence which confers on the licensee or on the licenses and`
  line `persons authorised by him, to the exclusion of all other persons (including the owner of the`
  line `copyright), any right comprised in the copyright in a work, and exclusive licensee shall be`
  line `construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(k) Government work means a work which is made or published by or under the direction or`
  line `control of--`
  line
  line `(i) the Government or any department of the Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) any Legislature in India;`
  line
  line `(iii) any court, tribunal or other judicial authority in India;`
  line
  line `^13[(I) Indian work means a literary, dramatic or musical work,--`
  line
  line `(i) the author of which is a citizen of India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which is first published in India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the author of which, in the case of an unpublished work, is, at the time of the making`
  line `of the work, a citizen of India;]`
  line
  line `^14[(m) infringing copy means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work, a reproduction thereof`
  line `otherwise than in the form of a cinematograph film;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a cinematographic film, a copy of the film made on any medium by any`
  line means;
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to a sound recording, any other recording embodying the same sound`
  line `recording, made by any means;`
  line
  line `(iv) in relation to a programme or performance in which such a broadcast reproduction`
  line `right or a performer's right subsists under the provisions of this Act, the sound recording or a`
  line `cinematographic film of such programme or performance,;`
  line
  line `if such reproduction, copy or sound recording is made or imported in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act;]`
  line
  line `(n) lecture includes address, speech and sermon;`
  line
  line `^15[(o) literary work includes computer programmes, tables and compilations including computer ^16[databases];]`
  line
  line `^17[(p) musical work means a work consisting of music and includes any graphical notation of`
  line `such work but does not include any words or any action intended to be sung, spoken or performed`
  line `with the music;]`
  line
  line `^18[(q) performance, in relation to performer's right, means any visual or acoustic presentation`
  line `made live by one or more performers;]`
  line
  line `^19[(qq) performer includes an actor, singer, musician, dancer, acrobat, juggler, conjurer, snake`
  line `charmer, a person delivering a lecture or any other person who makes a performance;]`
  line
  line `^20 *****/bh`
  line
  line `(s) photograph includes photo-lithograph and any work produced by any process analogous to`
  line `photography but does not include any part of a cinematograph film;`
  line
  line `(t) plate includes any stereotype or other plate, stone, block, mould, matrix, transfer,`
  line `negative, ^21[duplicating equipment] or other device used or intended to be used for printing or`
  line `reproducing copies of any work, and any matrix or other appliance by which ^22[sound recording] for the acoustic presentation of the work are or are intended to be made;`
  line
  line `^23[(u) “prescribed” means,—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to proceedings before a High Court, prescribed by rules made by the High`
  line `Court; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in other cases, prescribed by rules made under this Act;]`
  line
  line `^24[(uu) producer, in relation to a cinematograph film or sound recording, means a person who`
  line `takes the initiative and responsibility for making the work;]`
  line
  line ^25*****
  line
  line ^26*****
  line
  line `^27[(x) reprography means the making of copies of a work, by photocopying or similar means;`
  line
  line `^28[(xa) Right Management Information means,--`
  line
  line `(a) the title or other information identifying the work or performance;`
  line
  line `(b) the name of the author or performer;`
  line
  line `(c) the name and address of the owner of rights;`
  line
  line `(d) terms and conditions regarding the use of the rights; and`
  line
  line `(e) any number or code that represents the information referred to in sub-clauses (a) to (d),`
  line `but does not include any device or procedure intended to identify the user.`
  line
  line `(xx) sound recording means a recording of sounds from which such sounds may be produced`
  line `regardless of the medium on which such recording is made or the method by which the sounds are`
  line produced;]
  line
  line `^29(xxa) visual recording means the recording in any medium, by any method including the`
  line `storing of it by any electronic means, or moving images or of the representations thereof, from which they can be perceived, reproduced or communicated by any method.]`
  line
  line `(y) work means any of the following works, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work;`
  line
  line `(ii) a cinematograph film;`
  line
  line `(iii) ^22[sound recording];`
  line
  line `(z) work of joint authorship means a work produced by the collaboration of two or more`
  line `authors in which the contribution of one author is not distinct from the contribution of the other`
  line `author or authors;`
  line
  line `(za) work of sculpture includes casts and models.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word and omitted by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (aa) omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 10 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid.., for architectural work of art (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid.., for sub-clauses (v) and (vi) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `8. The words on any medium produced through a process from which a moving image may be any means omitted by Act 27 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (ff) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 2, for radio-diffusion (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 2, for clause (l) (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for clause (m) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (o) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 49 of 1999, s. 2, for data basis (w.e.f. 15-1-2000).`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for clause (p) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (q) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `19. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `20. Omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `21. Ins. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
  line
  line `22. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for record (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `23. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 10, for clause (u) (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `24. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `25. Omitted by Act 23 of 1983, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `26. Omitted by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `27. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (x) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `28 Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (14505)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Meaning of publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 3, for section 3 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14505&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Meaning of publication.--For the purposes of this Act, "publication" means making a work`
  line `available to the public by issue of copies or by communicating the work to the public.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (14506)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `When work not deemed to be published or performed in public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14506&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Except in relation to`
  line `infringement of copyright, a work shall not be deemed to be published or performed in public, if`
  line `published, or performed in public, without the licence of the owner of the copyright.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (14507)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `When work deemed to be first published in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14507&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, a work`
  line `published in India shall be deemed to be first published in India, notwithstanding that it has been`
  line `published simultaneously in some other country, unless such other country provides a shorter term of`
  line `copyright for such work; and a work shall be deemed to be published simultaneously in India and in`
  line `another country if the time between the publication in India and the publication in such other country does`
  line `not exceed thirty days or such other period as the Central Government may, in relation to any specified`
  line `country, determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (14508)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Certain disputes to be decided by Commercial Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14508&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Certain disputes to be decided by ^2[Commercial Court].--If any question arises--`
  line
  line `(a) whether a work has been published or as to the date on which a work was published for the purposes of Chapter V, or`
  line
  line `(b) whether the term of copyright for any work is shorter in any other country than that provided in respect of that work under this Act,`
  line
  line `it shall be referred to the ^2[Commercial Court] ^3****:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in the opinion of the ^2[Commercial Court], the issue of copies or communication to the public referred to in section 3 was of an insignificant nature, it shall not be deemed to be publication for the purposes of that section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 4, for section 6 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. The words and figures “constituted under section 11 whose decision thereon shall be final” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 10 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (14509)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Nationality of author where the making of unpublished work is extended over considerable period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14509&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where, in the case of an unpublished work, the making of the work is extended over a`
  line `considerable period, the author of the work shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to be a citizen`
  line `of, or domiciled in, that country of which he was a citizen or wherein he was domiciled during any`
  line `substantial part of that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (14510)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Domicile of Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14510&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, a body corporate shall be deemed to be`
  line `domiciled in India if it is incorporated under any law in force in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (14511)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Copyright Office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14511&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established for the purposes of this Act an office to be`
  line `called the Copyright Office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Copyright Office shall be under the immediate control of the Registrar of Copyrights who`
  line `shall act under the superintendence and direction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be a seal for the Copyright Office.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (14512)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Registrar and Deputy Registrars of Copyrights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14512&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint a`
  line `Registrar of Copyrights and may appoint one or more Deputy Registrars of Copyrights.`
  line
  line `(2) A Deputy Registrar of Copyrights shall discharge under the superintendence and direction of the`
  line `Registrar of Copyrights such functions of the Registrar under this Act as the Registrar may, from time to`
  line `time, assign to him; and any reference in this Act to the Registrar of Copyrights shall include a reference`
  line `to a Deputy Registrar of Copyrights when so discharging any such functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (14513)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Omitted.
  content `11. [Appellate Board].--Omitted by the Tribunal Reforms Act, 2021 (33 of 2021), s. 10 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
