obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (14514)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Omitted.
  content `12. [Powers and procedure of Appellate Board]. Omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14514&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (14515)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Works in which copyright subsists.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14515&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section and the other`
  line `provisions of this Act, copyright shall subsist throughout India in the following classes of works, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) original literary, dramatic, musical and artistic works;`
  line
  line `(b) cinematograph films; and`
  line
  line `(c) ^1[sound recording].`
  line
  line `(2) Copyright shall not subsist in any work specified in sub-section (1), other than a work to`
  line `which the provisions of section 40 or section 41 apply, unless--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a published work, the work is first published in India, or where the work is`
  line `first published outside India, the author is at the date of such publication, or in a case where the`
  line `author was dead at that date, was at the time of his death, a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of an unpublished work other than a ^2[work of architecture], the author is at the`
  line `date of making of the work a citizen of India or domiciled in India; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a ^2[work of architecture], the work is located in India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a work of joint authorship, the conditions conferring copyright`
  line `specified in this sub-section shall be satisfied by all the authors of the work.`
  line
  line `(3) Copyright shall not subsist`
  line
  line `(a) in any cinematograph film if a substantial part of the film is an infringement of the copyright`
  line `in any other work;`
  line
  line `(b) in any ^3[sound recording] made in respect of a literary, dramatic or musical work, if in making`
  line `the ^3[sound recording], copyright in such work has been infringed.`
  line
  line `(4) The copyright in a cinematograph film or a record shall not affect the separate copyright in any`
  line `work in respect of which or a substantial part of which, the film, or, as the case may be, the ^3[sound recording] is made.--`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of a ^3[work of architecture], copyright shall subsist only in the artistic character and`
  line `design and shall not extend to processes or methods of construction.--`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for "record" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "architectural work of art" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "record" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995)`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (14516)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Meaning of copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14516&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Meaning of copyright.-- For the purposes of this Act, copyright means the exclusive right subject to the provisions of this Act, to do or authorise the doing of any of the following acts in respect of a work or any substantial part thereof, namely--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a literary, dramatic or musical work, not being a computer programme,--`
  line
  line `(i) to reproduce the work in any material form including the storing of it in any medium by`
  line `electronic means;`
  line
  line `(ii) to issue copies of the work to the public not being copies already in circulation;`
  line
  line `(iii) to perform the work in public, or communicate it to the public;`
  line
  line `(iv) to make any cinematograph film or sound recording in respect of the work;`
  line
  line `(v) to make any translation of the work;`
  line
  line `(vi) to make any adaptation of the work;`
  line
  line `(vii) to do, in relation to a translation or an adaptation of the work, any of the acts specified in`
  line `relation to the work in sub-clauses (i) to (vi);`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a computer programme:`
  line
  line `(i) to do any of the acts specified in clause (a);`
  line
  line `^2[(ii) to sell or give on commercial rental or offer for sale or for commercial rental any copy of the computer programmer:`
  line
  line `Provided that such commercial rental does not apply in respect of computer programmes where the programme itself is not the essential object of the rental.]`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of an artistic work,--`
  line
  line `^3[(i) to reproduce the work in any material form including--`
  line
  line `(A) the storing of it in any medium by electronic or other means; or`
  line
  line `(B) depiction in three-dimensions of a two-dimensional work; or`
  line
  line `(C) depiction in two-dimensions of a three-dimensional work;]`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a cinematograph film,--`
  line
  line `^4[(i) to make a copy of the film, including--`
  line
  line `(A) a photograph of any image forming part thereof; or`
  line
  line `(B) storing of it in any medium by electronic or other means;]`
  line
  line `^5[(ii) to sell or give on commercial rental or offer for sale or for such rental, any copy of the film.]`
  line
  line `(iii) to communicate the film to the public;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a sound recording,--`
  line
  line `(i) to make any other sound recording embodying it ^6[including storing of it in any medium by electronic or other means];`
  line
  line `^7[(ii) to sell or give on commercial rental or offer for sale or for such rental, any copy of the sound recording;]`
  line
  line `(iii) to communicate the sound recording to the public.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a copy which has been sold once shall be deemed to be a copy already in circulation].`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for section 14 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1999, s. 3, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 15-1-2000)`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 5, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (14517)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Special provision regarding copyright in designs registered or capable of being registered under the Designs Act, 2000.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14517&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `15. Special provision regarding Copyright in designs registered or Capable of being registered under the ^1*** ^2[Designs Act, 2000 (16 of 2000)].--(1) Copyright shall not subsist under this Act in any`
  line `design which is registered under the ^1*** ^2[Designs Act, 2000 (16 of 2000)].`
  line
  line `(2) Copyright in any design, which is capable of being registered under the ^1*** ^2[Designs Act, 2000 (16 of 2000)] but which has not been so registered, shall cease as soon as any article to which the design has been applied has been reproduced more than fifty times by an industrial process by the owner of the copyright or, with his licence, by any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "Indian Patents and" omitted by Act 23 of 1983, s. 7 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 6, for "Designs Act, 1911 (2 of 1911)" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012)`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (14518)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `No copyright except as provided in this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14518&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to copyright or any`
  line `similar right in any work, whether published or unpublished, otherwise than under and in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act or of any other law for the time being in force, but nothing in this section shall`
  line `be construed as abrogating any right or jurisdiction to restrain a breach of trust or confidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (14519)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `First owner of copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14519&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the author of a work shall be`
  line `the first owner of the copyright therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a literary, dramatic or artistic work made by the author in the course of his`
  line `employment by the proprietor of a newspaper, magazine or similar periodical under a contract of`
  line `service or apprenticeship, for the purpose of publication in a newspaper, magazine or similar periodical, the said proprietor shall, in the absence of any agreement to the contrary, be the first`
  line `owner of the copyright in the work in so far as the copyright relates to the publication of the work`
  line `in any newspaper, magazine or similar periodical, or to the reproduction of the work for the`
  line `purpose of its being so published, but in all other respects the author shall be the first owner of the`
  line `copyright in the work;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the provisions of clause (a), in the case of a photograph taken, or a painting or`
  line `portrait drawn, or an engraving or a cinematograph film made, for valuable consideration at the`
  line `instance of any person, such person shall, in the absence of any agreement to the contrary, be the`
  line `first owner of the copyright therein;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a work made in the course of the authors employment under a contract of`
  line `service or apprenticeship, to which clause (a) or clause (b) does not apply, the employer shall, in`
  line `the absence of any agreement to the contrary, be the first owner of the copyright therein;`
  line
  line `^1[(cc) in the case of any address or speech delivered in public, the person who has delivered`
  line `such address or speech or if such person has delivered such address or speech on behalf of any`
  line `other person, such other person shall be the first owner of the copyright therein notwithstanding`
  line `that the person who delivers such address or speech, or, as the case may be, the person on whose`
  line `behalf such address or speech is delivered, is employed by any other person who arranges such`
  line `address or speech or on whose behalf or premises such address or speech is delivered;]`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a Government work, Government shall, in the absence of any agreement to`
  line `the contrary, be the first owner of the copyright therein;`
  line
  line `^1[(dd) in the case of a work made or first published by or under the direction or control of any public undertaking, such public undertaking shall, in the absence of any agreement to the contrary, be the first owner of the copyright therein.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this clause and section 28A, public undertaking means--`
  line
  line `(i) an undertaking owned or controlled by Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a Government company as defined in Section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) a body corporate established by or under any Central, Provincial or State Act;]`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a work to which the provisions of section 41 apply, the international`
  line `organisation concerned shall be the first owner of the copyright therein.`
  line
  line ^2[
  line `Provided that in case of any work incorporated in a cinematograph work, nothing contained in`
  line `clauses (b) and (c) shall affect the right of the author in the work referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 8 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 7 (w.e.f. 21-6-202).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (14520)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Assignment of copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14520&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of the copyright in an existing work or the prospective`
  line `owner of the copyright in a future work may assign to any person the copyright either wholly or partially`
  line `and either generally or subject to limitations and either for the whole term of the copyright or any part`
  line `thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of the assignment of copyright in any future work, the assignment shall take`
  line `effect only when the work comes into existence.`
  line
  line ^3[
  line `Provided further that no such assignment shall be applied to any medium or mode of exploitation of`
  line `the work which did not exit or was not in commercial use at the time when the assignment was made,`
  line `unless the assignment specifically referred to such medium or mode of exploitation of the work:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the author of the literary or musical work included in a cinematograph film shall`
  line `not assign or waive the right to receive royalties to be shared on an equal basis with the assignee of`
  line `copyright for the utilisation of such work in any form other than for the communication to the public of the work along with the cinematograph film in a cinema hall, except to the legal heirs of the authors or to`
  line `a copyright society for collection and distribution and any agreement to contrary shall be void:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the author of the literary or musical work included in the sound recording but not`
  line `forming part of any cinematograph film shall not assign or waive the right to receive royalties to be`
  line `shared on an equal basis with the assignee of copyright for any utilisation of such work except to the legal`
  line `heirs of the authors or to a collecting society for collection and distribution and any assignment to the`
  line `contrary shall be void.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where the assignee of a copyright becomes entitled to any right comprised in the copyright, the`
  line `assignee as respects the rights so assigned, and the assignor as respects the rights not assigned, shall be`
  line `treated for the purposes of this Act as the owner of copyright and the provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, the expression "assignee" as respects the assignment of the copyright in any future`
  line `work includes the legal representatives of the assignee, if the assignee dies before the work comes into`
  line existence.
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (14521)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Mode of assignment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14521&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] No assignment of the copyright in any work shall be valid unless it`
  line `is in writing signed by the assignor or by his duly authorised agent.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The assignment of copyright in any work shall identify such work, and shall specify the rights`
  line `assigned and the duration and territorial extent of such assignment.`
  line
  line `(3) The assignment of copyright in any work shall also specify the amount of ^3[`
  line `royalty and any other consideration payable], to the author or his legal heirs during the currency of the assignment and the`
  line `assignment shall be subject to revision, extension or termination on terms mutually agreed upon by the`
  line parties.
  line
  line `(4) Where the assignee does not exercise the rights assigned to him under any of the other`
  line `sub-sections of this section within period of one year from the date of assignment, the assignment in`
  line `respect of such right shall be deemed to have lapsed after the expiry of the said period unless otherwise`
  line `specified in the assignment.`
  line
  line `(5) If the period of assignment is not stated, it shall be deemed to be five years from the date of`
  line assignment.
  line
  line `(6) If the territorial extent of assignment of the rights is not specified, it shall be presumed to extend`
  line `within India.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) or`
  line `sub-section (6) shall be applicable to assignments made before the coming into force of the Copyright`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1994.`
  line
  line `^4[(8) The assignment of copyright in any work contrary to the terms and conditions of the rights`
  line `already assigned to a copyright society in which the author of the work is a member shall be void.`
  line
  line `(9) No assignment of copyright in any work to make a cinematograph film shall affect the right of the`
  line `author of the work to claim an equal share of royalties and consideration payable in case of utilisation of`
  line `the work in any form other than for the communication to the public of the work, along with the`
  line `cinematograph film in a cinema hall.`
  line
  line `(10) No assignment of the copyright in any work to make a sound recording which does not form part`
  line `of any cinematograph film shall affect the right of the author of the work to claim an equal share of`
  line `royalties and consideration payable for any utilisation of such work in any form.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Section 19 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 23 of 1983, s. 9 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 8, for section 19 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 9, for "royalty payable" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (14522)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 20
  title `Disputes with respect to assignment of copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14522&sectionno=19A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Disputes with respect to assignment of copyright.--(1) If an assignee fails to make sufficient exercise of the rights assigned to him, and such failure is not attributable to any act or omission of the assignor, then, the ^2[ Commercial Court] may, on receipt of a complaint from the assignor and after holding such inquiry as it may deem necessary, revoke such assignment.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises with respect to the assignment of any copyright, the ^2[Commercial Court] may, on receipt of a complaint from the aggrieved party and after holding such inquiry as it considers necessary, pass such order as it may deem fit including an order for the recovery of any royalty payable:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^2[Commercial Court] shall not pass any order under this sub-section to revoke the assignment unless it is satisfied that the terms of assignment are harsh to the assignor in case the assignor is also the author:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that, pending the disposal of an application for revocation of assignment under this sub-section, the ^2[Commercial Court] may pass such order, as it deems fit regarding implementation of the terms and conditions of assignment including any consideration to be paid for the enjoyment of the rights assigned:---`
  line
  line `Provided also that,] no order of revocation of assignment under this sub-section, shall be made within a period of five years from the date of such assignment.]`
  line
  line `^4[(3) Every complaint received under sub-section (2) shall be dealt with by the ^2[Commercial Court] as far as possible and efforts shall be made to pass the final order in the matter within a period of six months from the date of receipt of the complaint and any delay in compliance of the same, the ^2[Commercial Court] shall record the reasons thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 9, for section 19A (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.21, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 10, for Provided further that (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 10 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (14523)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Transmission of copyright in manuscript by testamentary disposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14523&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where under a`
  line `bequest a person is entitled to the manuscript of a literary, dramatic or musical work, or to an artistic`
  line `work, and the work was not published before the death of the testator, the bequest shall, unless the`
  line `contrary intention is indicated in the testator's will or any codicil thereto, be construed as including the`
  line `copyright in the work in so far as the testator was the owner of the copyright immediately before his`
  line death.
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the expression "manuscript" means the original document embodying`
  line `the work, whether written by hand or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (14524)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Right of author to relinquish copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14524&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The author of a work may relinquish all or any of`
  line `the rights comprised in the copyright in the work by giving notice in the prescribed form to ^1[the Registrar`
  line `of Copyrights or by way of public notice] and thereupon such rights shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3), cease to exist from the date of the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a notice under sub-section (1), the Registrar of Copyrights shall cause it to be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette and in such other manner as he may deem fit.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) The Registrar of Copyright shall, within fourteen days from the publication of the notice in the`
  line `Official Gazette, post the notice on the official website of the Copyright Office so as to remain in the`
  line `public domain for a period of not less than three years.]`
  line
  line `(3) The relinquishment of all or any of the rights comprised in the copyright in a work shall not affect any rights subsisting in favour of any person on the date of notice referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "Registrar of Copyright" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (14525)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Term of copyright in published literary, dramatic, musical and artistic works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14525&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Except as`
  line `otherwise hereinafter provided, copyright shall subsist in any literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work ^1*** published within the lifetime of the author until ^2[sixty years] from the beginning of the calendar`
  line `year next following the year in which the author dies.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section the reference to the author shall, in the case of a work of joint authorship, be construed as a reference to the author who dies last.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and words "(other than a photograph)" omitted by Act 27 of 2012, s. 12 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 28-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (14526)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Term of copyright in anonymous and pseudonymous works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14526&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work (other than a photograph), which is published anonymously or pseudonymously, copyright shall subsist until ^1[sixty years] from the beginning of the calendar year next following the year in which the work is first published:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the identity of the author is disclosed before the expiry of the said period, copyright shall subsist until ^1[sixty years] from the beginning of the calendar year next following the year in which the author dies.`
  line
  line `(2) In sub-section (1), references to the author shall, in the case of an anonymous work of joint authorship, be construed,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the identity of one of the authors is disclosed, as references to that author;`
  line
  line `(b) where the identity of more authors than one is disclosed, as references to the author who dies last from amongst such authors.`
  line
  line `(3) In sub-section (1), references to the author shall, in the case of a pseudonyms work of joint authorship, be construed,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the names of one or more (but not all) of the authors are pseudonyms and his or their identity is not disclosed, as references to the author whose name is not a pseudonym, or, if the names of two or more of the authors are not pseudonyms, as references to such of those authors who dies last;`
  line
  line `(b) where the names of one or more (but not all) of the authors are pseudonyms and the identity of one or more of them is disclosed, as references to the author who dies last from amongst the authors whose names are not pseudonyms and the authors whose names are pseudonyms and are disclosed; and`
  line
  line `(c) where the names of all the authors are pseudonyms and the identity of one of them is disclosed, as references to the author whose identity is disclosed or if the identity of two or more of such authors is disclosed, as references to such of those authors who dies last.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the identity of an author shall be deemed to have been disclosed, if either the identity of the author is disclosed publicly by both the author and the publisher or is otherwise established to the satisfaction of the ^2[Commercial Court] by that author.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for fifty years (w.e.f. 28-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.21, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (14527)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Term of copyright in posthumous work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14527&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of a literary, dramatic or musical work`
  line `or an engraving, in which copyright subsists at the date of the death of the author or, in the case of any`
  line `such work of joint authorship, at or immediately before the date of the death of the author who dies last,`
  line `but which, or any adaptation of which, has not been published before that date, copyright shall subsist`
  line `until ^1[sixty years] from the beginning of the calendar year next following the year in which the work is`
  line `first published or, where an adaptation of the work is published in any earlier year, from the beginning of`
  line `the calendar year next following that year.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section a literary, dramatic or musical work or an adaptation of any such`
  line `work shall be deemed to have been published, if it has been performed in public or if any ^2[sound recordings] made in respect of the work have been sold to the public or have been offered for sale to the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 28-10-1991).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for "record" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (14528)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14528&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `[Term of copyright in photographs.] Omitted by the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 2012`
  line `(27 of 2012), s. 13 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (14529)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Term of copyright in cinematograph films.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 28-10-1991)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14529&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a cinematograph film, copyright`
  line `shall subsists until ^1[sixty years] from the beginning of the calendar year next following the year in which`
  line `the film is published.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (14530)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Term of copyright in sound recording.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14530&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `In the case a ^1[sound recording] copyright shall subsist`
  line `until ^2[sixty years] from the beginning of the calendar year next following the year in which the ^1[sound recording] is published.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for "record" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 28-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (14531)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Term of copyright Government works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 28-10-1991)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14531&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `In the case of Government work, where Government`
  line `is the first owner of the copyright therein, copyright shall subsist until ^1[sixty years] from the beginning of`
  line `the calendar year next following the year in which the work is first published.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (14532)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 30
  title `Term of copyright in works of public undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14532&sectionno=28A&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[28A. Term of copyright in works of public undertakings.--In the case of a work, where a public undertaking is the first owner of the copyright therein, copyright shall subsist until ^2[sixty years] from the`
  line `beginning of the calendar year next following the year in which the work is first published.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 11 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 28-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (14533)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Term of copyright in works of international organisations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 1992, s. 2, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 28-10-1991).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14533&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a work of an`
  line `international organisation to which the provisions of section 41 apply, copyright shall subsist until ^1[sixty years] from the beginning of the calendar year next following the year in which the work is first`
  line published.
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (14534)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Licences by owners of copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 14, for "writing signed by him" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14534&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The owner of the copyright in any existing work of the`
  line `prospective owner of the copyright in any future work may grant any interest in the right by licence in`
  line `^1[writing by him] or by his duly authorised agent:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a licence relating to copyright in any future work, the licence shall take`
  line `effect only when the work comes into existence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where a person to whom a licence relating to copyright in any future work is granted`
  line `under this section dies before the work comes into existence, his legal representatives shall, in the absence`
  line `of any provision to the contrary in the licence, be entitled to the benefit of the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (14535)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 33
  title `Application of sections 19.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14535&sectionno=30A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Application of ^2[section 19].--The provisions of sections 19 and 19A shall, with any necessary adaptations and modifications, apply in relation to a licence under section 30 as they apply in`
  line `relation to assignment of copyright in a work.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 10 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 15, for "section 19 and 19A" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (14536)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Compulsory licence in works withheld from public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14536&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time during the term of`
  line `copyright in ^1[any work] which has been published or performed in public, a complaint is made to the`
  line `^2[Commecial Court] that the owner of copyright in the work--`
  line
  line `(a) has refused to republish or allow the republication of the work or has refused to allow the`
  line `performance in public of the work, and by reason of such refusal the work is withheld from the`
  line `public; or`
  line
  line `(b) has refused to allow communication to the public by ^3[broadcast] of such work or in the case`
  line `of a ^4[sound recording] the work recorded in such ^4[sound recording], on terms which the`
  line `complainant considers reasonable,`
  line
  line `the ^2[Commercial Court], after giving to the owner of the copyright in the work a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard and after holding such inquiry as it may deem necessary, may, if it is satisfied that the`
  line `grounds for such refusal are not reasonable, direct the Registrar of Copyrights to grant to the complainant`
  line `a licence to republish the work, perform the work in public or communicate the work to the public by`
  line `^4[broadcast], as the case may be, subject to payment to the owner of the copyright of such compensation`
  line `and subject to such other terms and conditions as the ^2[Commercial Court] may determine; and thereupon`
  line `the Registrar of Copyrights shall grant the ^5[licence to such person or persons who, in the opinion of the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court], is or are qualified to do so] in accordance with the directions of the ^2[Commercial Court], on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^6 * * * * *.`
  line
  line `^7 * * * * *.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for any Indian work (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 1994, s. 2, for radio-diffusion (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by 38 of 1994, s. 16, for record (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 16, for licence to the complainant (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `6. The Explanation omitted by Act 27 of 2012, s. 16, (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Omitted by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (14537)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 35
  title `Compulsory licence in unpublished or published works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14537&sectionno=31A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Compulsory licence in unpublished ^2[or published works].--`
  line `^3[(1) Where, in the case of any unpublished work or any work published or communicated to the public and the work is withheld from the public in India, the author is dead or unknown or cannot be traced, or the owner of the copyright in such work cannot be found, any person may apply to the ^4[Commecial Court] for a licence to publish or communicate to the public such work or a translation thereof in any language.]`
  line
  line `(2) Before making an application under sub-section (1), the applicant shall publish his proposal in one issue of a daily newspaper in the English language having circulation in the major part of the country and where the application is for the publication of a translation in any language, also in one issue of any daily newspaper in that language.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such application shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall be accompanied with a copy of the advertisement issued under sub-section (2) and such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application is made to the ^4[Commercial Court] under this section, it may after holding such inquiry as may be prescribed, direct the Registrar of Copyrights to grant to the applicant a licence to publish the work or a translation thereof in the language mentioned in the application subject to the payment of such royalty and subject to such other terms and conditions as the ^4[Commercial Court] may determine, and thereupon the Registrar of Copyrights shall grant the licence to the applicant in accordance with the direction of the ^4[Commercial Court].`
  line
  line `(5) Where a licence is granted under this section, the Registrar of Copyrights may, by order, direct the applicant to deposit the amount of the royalty determined by the ^4[Commercial Court] in the public account of India or in any other account specified by the ^4[Commercial Court] so as to enable the owner of the copyright or, as the case may be, his heirs, executors or the legal representatives to claim such royalty at any time.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section, in the case of a work referred to in sub-section (1), if the original author is dead, the Central Government may, if it considers that the publication of the work is desirable in the national interest, require the heirs, executors or legal representatives of the author to publish such work within such period as may be specified by it.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any work is not published within the period specified by the Central Government under sub-section (6), the ^4[Commercial Court] may, on an application made by any person for permission to publish the work and after hearing the parties concerned, permit such publication on payment of such royalty as the ^4[Commercial Court] may, in the circumstances of such case, determine in the prescribed manner.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_footnotes:
  string
