obj_root_law_sections_31_b:
  sectionId (14538)
  sectionNo 31B
  orderNo 36
  title `Compulsory licence for benefit of disabled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14538&sectionno=31B&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[31B. Compulsory licence for benefit of disabled.---(1) Any person working for the benefit of persons with disability on a profit basis or for business may apply to the ^2[ACommercial Court], in such form and manner and accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed, for a compulsory licence to published any work in which copyright subsists for the benefit of such persons, in a case to which clause (zb) of sub-section (1) of section 52 does not apply and the ^2[Commercial Court] shall dispose of such application within a period of two months from the receipt of the application.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Commercial Court] may, on receipt of an application under sub-section (1), inquire, or direct such inquiry as it considers necessary to establish the credentials of the applicant and satisfy itself that the application has been made in good faith.`
  line
  line `(3) If the ^2[Commercial Court] is satisfied, after giving to the owners of rights in the work a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after holding such inquiry as it may deem necessary, that a compulsory licence needs to be issued to make the work available to the disabled, it may direct the Registrar of Copyright to grant to the applicant such a licence to publish the work.`
  line
  line `(4) Every compulsory licence issued under this section shall specify the means and format of publication, the period during which the compulsory licence may be exercised and, in the case of issue of copies, the number of copies that may be issued including the rate or royalty:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the ^2[Commercial Court] issued such a compulsory licence it may, on a further application and after giving reasonable opportunity to the owners of rights, extend the period of such compulsory licence and allow the issue of more copies as it may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.160, for Copyright Board (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_c:
  sectionId (14539)
  sectionNo 31C
  orderNo 37
  title `Statutory licence for cover versions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14539&sectionno=31C&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_31_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[31C. Statutory licence for cover versions.---(1) Any person desirous of making a cover version, being a sound recording in respect of any literary, dramatic or musical work, where sound recordings of that work have been made by or with the licence or consent of the owner of the right in the work, may do so subject to the provisions of this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sound recordings shall be in the same medium as the last recording, unless the medium of the last recording is no longer in current commercial use.`
  line
  line `(2) The person making the sound recordings shall give prior notice of his intention to make the sound recordings in the manner as may be prescribed, and provide in advance copies of all covers or labels with which the sound recordings are to be sold, and pay in advance, to the owner of rights in each work royalties in respect of all copies to be made by him, at the rate fixed by the ^2[Commercial Court] in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sound recordings shall not be sold or issued in any form of packaging or with any cover or label which is likely to mislead or confuse the public as to their identity, and in particular shall not contain the name or depict in any way any performer of an earlier sound recording of the same work or any cinematograph film in which sound recording was incorporated and, further, shall state on the cover that it is a cover version made under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The person making such sound recordings shall not make any alteration in the literary or musical work which has not been made previously by or with the consent of the owner of rights, or which is not technically necessary for the purpose of making the sound recordings:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sound recordings shall not be made until the expiration of five calendar years after the end of the year in which the first sound recordings of the work was made.`
  line
  line `(4) One royalty in respect of such sound recordings shall be paid for a minimum of fifty thousand copies of each work during each calendar year in which copies of it are made:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^2[Commercial Court] may, by general order, fix a lower minimum in respect of works in a particular language or dialect having regard to the potential circulation of such works.`
  line
  line `(5) The person making such sound recordings shall maintain such registers and books of account in respect thereof, including full details of existing stock as may be prescribed and shall allow the owner of rights or his duly authorised agent or representative to inspect all records and books of account relating to such sound recording:`
  line
  line `Provided that if on a complaint brought before the ^2[Commercial Court] to the effect that the owner of rights has not been paid in full for any sound recordings purporting to be made in pursuance of this section, the ^2[Commercial Court] is, prima facie, satisfied that the complaint is genuine, it may pass an order ex parte directing the person making the sound recording to cease from making further copies and, after holding such inquiry as it considers necessary, make such further order as it may deem fit, including an order for payment of royalty.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section cover version means a sound recording made in accordance with this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 18 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_d:
  sectionId (14540)
  sectionNo 31D
  orderNo 38
  title `Statutory licence for broadcasting of literary and musical works and sound recording.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14540&sectionno=31D&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_31_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[31D. Statutory licence for broadcasting of literary and musical works and sound recording.--(1) Any broadcasting organisation desirous of communicating to the public by way of a broadcast or by way of performance of a literary or musical work and sound recording which has already been published may do so subject to the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The broadcasting organisation shall give prior notice, in such manner as may be prescribed, of its intention to broadcast the work stating the duration and territorial coverage of the broadcast, and shall pay to the owner of rights in each work royalties in the manner and at the rate fixed by the ^2[Commercial Court].`
  line
  line `(3) The rates of royalties for radio broadcasting shall be different from television broadcasting and the ^2[Commercial Court] shall fix separate rates for radio broadcasting and television broadcasting.`
  line
  line `(4) In fixing the manner and the rate of royalty under sub-section (2), the ^2[Commercial Court] may require the broadcasting organisation to pay an advance to the owners of rights.`
  line
  line `(5) The names of the authors of the principal performers of the work shall, except in case of the broadcasting organisation communicating such work by way of performance, be announced with the broadcast.`
  line
  line `(6) No fresh alteration to any literary or musical work, which is not technically necessary for the purpose of broadcasting, other than shortening the work for convenience of broadcast, shall be made without the consent of the owners of rights.`
  line
  line `(7) The broadcasting organisation shall--`
  line
  line `(a) maintain such records and books of account, and render to the owners of rights such reports and accounts; and`
  line
  line `(b) allow the owner of rights or his duly authorised agent or representative to inspect all records and books of account relating to such broadcast,`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) Nothing in this section shall affect the operation of any licence issued or any agreement entered into before the commencement of the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 2012.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 18 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (14541)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 39
  title `Licence to produce and publish translations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14541&sectionno=32&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person may apply to the ^1[Commercial Courtc] for a licence to produce and publish a translation of a literary or dramatic work in any language ^2[after a period of seven years from the first publication of the work].`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any person may apply to the ^1[Appellate Board] for a licence to produce and publish a translation, in printed or analogous forms of reproduction, of a literary or dramatic work, other than an Indian work, in any language in general use in India after a period of three years from the first publication of such work, if such translation is required for the purposes of teaching, scholarship or research:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such translation is in a language not in general use in any developed country, such application may be made after a period of one year from such publication.`
  line
  line `(2) Every ^3[application under this section] shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall state the proposed retail price of a copy of the translation of the work.`
  line
  line `(3) Every applicant for a licence under this section shall, along with his application, deposit with the Registrar of Copyrights such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application is made to the ^1[Commercial Court] under this section, it may, after holding such inquiry as may be prescribed, grant to the applicant a licence, not being an exclusive licence, to produce and publish a translation of the work in the language mentioned in ^4[the application--`
  line
  line `(i) subject to the condition that the applicant shall pay to the owner of the copyright in the work royalties in respect of copies of the translation of the work sold to the public, calculated at such rate as the ^1[Commercial Court] may, in the circumstances of each case, determine in the prescribed manner; and`
  line
  line `(ii) where such licence is granted on an application under sub-section (1A), subject also to the condition that the licence shall not extend to the export of copies of the translation of the work outside India and every copy of such translation shall contain a notice in the language of such translation that the copy is available for distribution only in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in clause (ii) shall apply to the export by Government or any authority under the Government of copies of such translation in a language other than English, French or Spanish or to any country if--`
  line
  line `(1) such copies are sent to citizens of India residing outside India or to any association of such citizens outside India; or`
  line
  line `(2) such copies are meant to be used for purposes of teaching, scholarship or research and not for any commercial purpose; and`
  line
  line `(3) in either case, the permission for such export has been given by the Government of that country:]`
  line
  line `^5[Provided further that no licence under this section] shall be granted, unless--`
  line
  line `(a) a translation of the work in the language mentioned in the application has not been published by the owner of the copyright in the work or any person authorised by him, ^6[within seven years or three years or one year, as the case may be, of the first publication of the work], or if a translation has been so published, it has been out of print;`
  line
  line `(b) the applicant has proved to the satisfaction of the ^1[Commercial Court] that he had requested and had been denied authorisation by the owner of the copyright to produce and publish such translation, or that ^7[he was, after due diligence on his part, unable to find] the owner of the copyright;`
  line
  line `(c) where the applicant was unable to find the owner of the copyright, he had sent a copy of his request for ^8[such authorisation by registered air mail post to the publisher whose name appears from the work, and in the case of an application for a licence under sub-section (1)], not less than two months before ^9[such application];`
  line
  line `^10[(cc) a period of six months in the case of an application under sub-section (1A) (not being an application under the proviso thereto), or nine months in the case of an application under the proviso to that sub-section, has elapsed from the date of making the request under clause (b) of this proviso or where a copy of the request has been sent under clause (c) of this proviso, from the date of sending of such copy, and the translation of the work in the language mentioned in the application has not been published by the owner of the copyright in the work or any person authorised by him within the said period of six months or nine months, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(ccc) in the case of any application made under sub-section (1A)--`
  line
  line `(i) the name of the author and the title of the particular edition of the work proposed to be translated are printed on all the copies of the translation;`
  line
  line `(ii) if the work is composed mainly of illustrations, the provisions of section 32A are also complied with;]`
  line
  line `(d) the ^1[Commercial Court] is satisfied that the applicant is competent to produce and publish a correct translation of the work and possesses the means to pay to the owner of the copyright the royalties payable to him under this section;`
  line
  line `(e) the author has not withdrawn from circulation copies of the work; and`
  line
  line `(f) an opportunity of being heard is given, wherever practicable, to the owner of the copyright in the work.`
  line
  line `^11[(5) Any broadcasting authority may apply to the ^1[Commercial Court] for a licence to produce and publish the translation of--`
  line
  line `(a) a work referred to in sub-section (1A) and published in printed or analogous forms of reproduction; or`
  line
  line `(b) any text incorporated in audio-visual fixations prepared and published solely for the purpose of systematic instructional activities, for broadcasting such translation for the purposes of teaching or for the dissemination of the results of specialised, technical or scientific research to the experts in any particular field.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of sub-sections (2) to (4) in so far as they are relatable to an application under sub-section (1A), shall, with the necessary modifications, apply to the grant of a licence under sub-section (5) and such licence shall not also be granted unless`
  line
  line `(a) the translation is made from a work lawfully acquired;`
  line
  line `(b) the broadcast is made through the medium of sound and visual recordings;`
  line
  line `(c) such recording has been lawfully and exclusively made for the purpose of broadcasting in India by the applicant or by other broadcasting agency;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) the translation and the broadcasting of such translation are not used for any commercial purposes.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) developed country means a country which is not a developing country;`
  line
  line `(b) developing country means a country which is for the time being regarded as such in conformity with the practice of the General Assembly of the United Nations;`
  line
  line `(c) purposes of research does not include purposes of industrial research, or purposes of research by bodies corporate (not being bodies corporate owned or controlled by Government) or other association or body of persons for commercial purposes;`
  line
  line `(d) purposes of teaching, research or scholarship includes--`
  line
  line `(i) purposes of instructional activity at all levels in educational, institutions, including Schools, Colleges, Universities and tutorial institutions; and`
  line
  line `(ii) purposes of all other types of organised educational activity.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for Appellate Board (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 13 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 13,ibid., for such application (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 13, for certain words (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 13, for Provided that no such licence (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 13, iibid., for within seven years of the first publication of the work (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for he was unable to find (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for such authorisation to the publisher whose name appears from the work (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for the application for the licence (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 13 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (14542)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 40
  title `Licence to reproduce and publish works for certain purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14542&sectionno=32A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [32A. Licence to reproduce and publish works for certain purposes.-- (1) Where, after the expiration of the relevant period from the date of the first publication of an edition of a literary, scientific or artistic work,--`
  line
  line `(a) the copies of such edition are not made available in India; or`
  line
  line `(b) such copies have not been put on sale in India for a period of six months,`
  line
  line `to the public, or in connection with systematic instructional activities at a price reasonably related to that`
  line `normally charged in India for comparable works by the owner of the right of reproduction or by any person authorised by him in this behalf, any person may apply to the ^2[Commercial Court] for a licence to`
  line `reproduce and publish such work in printed or analogous forms of reproduction at the price at which such`
  line `edition is sold or at a lower price for the purposes of systematic instructional activities.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such application shall be made in such form as may be prescribed and shall state the`
  line `proposed retail price of a copy of the work to be reproduced.`
  line
  line `(3) Every applicant for a licence under this section shall, along with his application, deposit with the`
  line `Registrar of Copyrights such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application is made to the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court] under this section, it may, after holding such`
  line `inquiry as may be prescribed, grant to the applicant a licence, not being an exclusive licence, to produce`
  line `and publish a reproduction of the work mentioned in the application subject to the conditions that,--`
  line
  line `(i) the applicant shall pay to the owner of the copyright in the work royalties in respect of copies`
  line `of the reproduction of the work sold to the public, calculated at such rate as the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court] may,`
  line `in the circumstances of each case, determine in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(ii) a licence granted under this section shall not extend to the export of copies of the reproduction`
  line `of the work outside India and every copy of such reproduction shall contain a notice that the copy is`
  line `available for distribution only in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such licence shall be granted unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the applicant has proved to the satisfaction of the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court] that he had requested`
  line `and had been denied authorisation by the owner of the copyright in the work to reproduce and`
  line `publish such work or that he was, after due diligence on his part, unable to find such owner;`
  line
  line `(b) where the applicant was unable to find the owner of the copyright, he had sent a copy of`
  line `his request for such authorisation by registered air-mail post to the publisher whose name appears`
  line `from the work not less than three months before the application for the licence;`
  line
  line `(c) the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court] is satisfied that the applicant is competent to reproduce and publish`
  line `an accurate reproduction of the work and possesses the means to pay the owner of the copyright`
  line `the royalties payable to him under this section;`
  line
  line `(d) the applicant undertakes to reproduce and publish the work at such price as may be fixed`
  line `by the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court], being a price reasonably related to the price normally charged in India`
  line `for works of the same standard on the same or similar subjects;`
  line
  line `(e) a period of six months in the case of an application for the reproduction and publication of`
  line `any work of natural science, physical science, mathematics or technology, or a period of three`
  line `months in the case of an application for the reproduction and publication of any other work, has`
  line `elapsed from the date of making the request under clause (a), or where a copy of the request has`
  line `been sent under clause (b), from the date of sending of a copy, and a reproduction of the work has`
  line `not been published by the owner of the copyright in the work or any person authorised by him`
  line `within the said period of six months or, three months, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) the name of the author and the title of the particular edition of the work proposed to be`
  line `reproduced are printed on all the copies of the reproduction;`
  line
  line `(g) the author has not withdrawn from circulation copies of the work; and`
  line
  line `(h) an opportunity of being heard is given, wherever practicable, to the owner of the`
  line `copyright in the work.`
  line
  line `(5) No licence to reproduce and publish the translation of a work shall be granted under this section`
  line `unless such translation has been published by the owner of the right of translation or any person`
  line `authorised by him and the translation is not in a language in general use in India.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section shall also apply to the reproduction and publication, or translation`
  line `into a language in general use in India, of any text incorporated in audio-visual fixations prepared and`
  line `published solely for the purpose of systematic instructional activities.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this section, relevant period, in relation to any work,`
  line `means a period of--`
  line
  line `(a) seven years from the date of the first publication of that work, where the application is`
  line `for the reproduction and publication of any work of, or relating to, fiction, poetry, drama,`
  line `music or art;`
  line
  line `(b) three years from the date of the first publication of that work, where the application is`
  line `for the reproduction and publication of any work of, or relating to, natural science, physical`
  line `science, mathematics or technology; and`
  line
  line `(c) five years from the date of the first publication of that work, in any other case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 13 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (14543)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 41
  title `Termination of licences issued under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 13 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14543&sectionno=32B&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[32B. Termination of licences issued under this Chapter.-- (1) If, at any time after the granting of a`
  line `licence to produce and publish the translation of a work in any language under sub-section (1A) of`
  line `section 32 (hereafter in this sub-section referred to as the licensed work), the owner of the copyright in the`
  line `work or any person authorised by him publishes a translation of such work in the same language and`
  line `which is substantially the same in content at a price reasonably related to the price normally charged in`
  line `India for the translation of works of the same standard on the same or similar subject, the licence so`
  line `granted shall be terminated:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such termination shall take effect until after the expiry of a period of three months`
  line `from the date of service of a notice in the prescribed manner on the person holding such licence by the`
  line `owner of the right of translation intimating the publication of the translation as aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided further that copies of the licensed work produced and published by the person holding such`
  line `licence before the termination of the licence takes effect may continue to be sold or distributed until the`
  line `copies already produced and published are exhausted.`
  line
  line `(2) If, at any time after the granting of a licence to produce and publish the reproduction or translation`
  line `of any work under section 32A, the owner of the right of reproduction or any person authorised by him`
  line `sells or distributes copies of such work or a translation thereof, as the case may be, in the same language`
  line `and which is substantially the same in content at a price reasonably related to the price normally charged`
  line `in India for works of the same standard on the same or similar subject, the licence so granted shall be`
  line `terminated:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such termination shall take effect until after the expiry of a period of three months`
  line `from the date of service of a notice in the prescribed manner on the person holding the licence by the`
  line `owner of the right of reproduction intimating the sale or distribution of the copies of the editions of work`
  line `as aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any copies already reproduced by the licensee before such termination takes`
  line `effect may continue to be sold or distributed until the copies already produced are exhausted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (14544)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 42
  title `Registration of copyright society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14544&sectionno=33&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[33. Registration of Copyright society.-- (1) No person or association of persons shall, after coming`
  line `into force of the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 1994 commence or, carry on the business of issuing or`
  line `granting licences in respect of any work in which copyright subsists or in respect of any other rights`
  line `conferred by this Act except under or in accordance with the registration granted under sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided that an owner of copyright shall, in his individual capacity, continue to have the right to`
  line `grant licences in respect of his own works consistent with his obligations as a member of the registered`
  line `copyright society:`
  line
  line `^2[ Provided further that the business of issuing or granting license in respect of literary, dramatic,`
  line `musical and artistic works incorporated in a cinematograph films or sound recording shall be carried out`
  line `only through a copyright society duly registered under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also] that a performing rights society functioning in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 33 on the date immediately before the coming into force of the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 1994 (38 of 1994) shall be deemed to be a copyright society for the purposes of this Chapter and every such society shall get itself registered within a period of one year form the date of commencement of the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 1994.`
  line
  line `(2) Any association of persons who fulfils such conditions as may be prescribed may apply for`
  line `permission to do the business specified in sub-section (1) to the Registrar of Copyrights who shall submit`
  line `the application to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, having regard to the interests of the authors and other owners of`
  line `rights under this Act, the interest and convenience of the public and in particular of the groups of persons`
  line `who are most likely to seek licences in respect of the relevant rights and the ability and professional`
  line `competence of the applicants, register such association of persons as a copyright society subject to such conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not ordinarily register more than one copyright society to do business in respect of the same class of Works.`
  line
  line `^3[(3A) The registration granted to a copyright society under sub-section (3) shall be for a period of`
  line `five years and may be renewed from time to time before the end of every five years on a request in the`
  line `prescribed form and the Central Government may renew the registration after considering the report of`
  line `Registrar of Copyright on the working of the copyright society under section 36:`
  line
  line `Provided that the renewal of the registration of a copyright society shall be subject to the continued`
  line `collective control of the copyright society being shared with the authors of works in their capacity as`
  line `owners of copyrights or of the right to receive royalty:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every copyright society already registered before the coming into force of the`
  line `Copyright (Amendment) Act, 2012 (27 of 2012) shall get itself registered under this Chapter within a`
  line `period of one years form the date of commencement of the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 2012.]`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, if it is satisfied that a copyright society is being managed in a`
  line `manner detrimental to the interests of the ^4[authors and other owners of rights] concerned, cancel the registration of such society after such inquiry as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Central Government is of the opinion that in the interest of the ^4[authors and other owners of rights] concerned ^5[or for non-compliance of sections 33A, sub-section (3) of section 35 or and section 36 of any change carried out in the instrument by which the copyright society is established or incorporated and registered by the Central Government without prior notice to it], is necessary so to do it may, by order suspend the registration of such society pending inquiry for such period not exceeding one year as may be specified in such order under sub-section (4) and that Government shall appoint an administrator to discharge the functions of the copyright society.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 11, for Chapter VII (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 19, for Provided that (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 19 ibid, (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for owner of rights (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (14545)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 43
  title `Tariff Scheme by copyright societies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14545&sectionno=33A&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[33A. Tariff Scheme by copyright societies.--(1) Every copyright society shall publish its tariff scheme in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who is aggrieved by the tariff scheme may appeal to the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court] and the Board may, it satisfied after holding such inquiry as it may consider necessary, make such orders as may be required to remove any unreasonable element, anomaly or inconsistency therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that the aggrieved person shall pay to the copyright society any fee as may be prescribed that has fallen due before making an appeal to the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court] and shall continue to pay such fee until the appeal is decided, and the Board shall not issue any order staying the collection of such fee pending disposal of the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the ^2[Commercial Court] may after hearing the parties fix an interim tariff and direct the aggrieved parties to make the payment according pending disposal of the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. . Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (14546)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 44
  title `Administration of rights of owner by copyright society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14546&sectionno=34&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Administration of rights of owner by copyright society.--(1) Subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed,--`
  line
  line `(a) a copyright society may accept from an ^2[author and other owners of right] exclusive`
  line `authorisation to administer any right in any work by issue of licences or collection of licence fees or`
  line `both; and`
  line
  line `(b) an ^2[author and other owners of right] shall have the right to withdraw such authorisation`
  line `without prejudice to the rights of the copyright society under any contract.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be competent for a copyright society to enter into agreement with any foreign society or`
  line `organisation administering rights corresponding to rights under this Act, to entrust to such foreign society`
  line `or organisation the administration in any foreign country of rights administered by the said copyright`
  line `society in India, or for administering in India the rights administered in a foreign country by such foreign`
  line `society or organisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such society or organisation shall permit any discrimination in regard to the terms of`
  line `licence or the distribution of fees collected between rights in Indian and other works.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, a copyright society may--`
  line
  line `(i) issue licences under section 30 in respect of any rights under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) collect fees in pursuance of such licences;`
  line
  line `(iii) distribute such fees among ^2[author and other owners of right] after making deductions for`
  line `its own expenses;`
  line
  line `(iv) perform any other functions consistent with the provisions of section 35.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 11, for Chapter VII (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 21, for "owner of rights" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012)`
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (14547)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 45
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 11, for Chapter VII (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14547&sectionno=34A&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[34A[Payment of remunerations by copyright society.] Omitted by the Copyright (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2012 (27 of 2012), s. 22 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (14548)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 46
  title `Control over the copyright society by the author and other owners of rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14548&sectionno=35&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[35. Control over the copyright society by the ^2[author and other owners of right].--(1) Every`
  line `copyright society shall be subject to the collective control of the owners of rights under this Act whose`
  line `rights it administers (not being ^2[author and other owners of right] under this Act administered by a`
  line `foreign society or organisation referred to in sub-section (2) of section 34) and shall, in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed,--`
  line
  line `(a) obtain the approval of such owners of rights for its procedures of collection and distribution of`
  line fees;
  line
  line `(b) obtain their approval for the utilisation of any amounts collected as fees for any purpose other`
  line `than distribution to the owner of rights; and`
  line
  line `(c) provide to such owners regular, full and detailed information concerning all its activities, in`
  line `relation to the administration of their rights.`
  line
  line `(2) All fees distributed among the ^2[author and other owners of right] shall, as far as may be, be`
  line `distributed in proportion to the actual use of their works.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every copyright society shall have a governing body with such number of persons elected from`
  line `among the members of the society consisting of equal number of authors and owners of work for the`
  line `purpose of the administration of the society as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(4) All members of copyright society shall enjoy equal membership rights and there shall be no`
  line `discrimination between authors and owners of rights in the distribution of royalties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 11, for Chapter VII (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 23, for "owner of rights" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (14549)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 47
  title `Submission of returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 11, for Chapter VII (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14549&sectionno=36&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Submission of returns and reports.--(1) Every copyright shall submit to the Registrar of`
  line `Copyrights such returns as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any officer duly authorised by the Central Government in this behalf may call for any report and also call for any records of any copyright society for the purpose of satisfying himself that the fees collected by the society in respect of rights administered by it are being utilised or distributed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_36_a:
  sectionId (14550)
  sectionNo 36A
  orderNo 48
  title `Rights and liabilities of performing rights societies.`
  content `^1[36A. Rights and liabilities of performing rights societies.--Nothing in this Chapter shall affect any rights or liabilities in any work in connection with a ^2[copyright society] which had accrued or were incurred on or before the day prior to the commencement of ^3[the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 2012], or any legal proceedings in respect of any such rights or liabilities pending on that day.]`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14550&sectionno=36A&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_36_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 11, for Chapter VII (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 24, for "performing rights society" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 24,ibid., for "the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 1994 (38 of 1994)" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (14551)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 49
  title `Broadcast reproduction right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14551&sectionno=37&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1, ^2[37. Broadcast reproduction right.-- (1) Every broadcasting organisation shall have a special right`
  line `to be known as “broadcast reproduction right” in respect of its broadcasts.`
  line
  line `(2) The broadcast reproduction right shall subsist until twenty-five years from the beginning of the`
  line `calendar year next following the year in which the broadcast is made.`
  line
  line `(3) During the continuance of a broadcast reproduction right in relation to any broadcast, any person`
  line `who, without the licence of the owner of the right does any of the following acts of the broadcast or any`
  line `substantial part thereof,--`
  line
  line `(a) re-broadcast the broadcast; or`
  line
  line `(b) causes the broadcast to be heard or seen by the public on payment of any charges; or`
  line
  line `(c) makes any sound recording or visual recording of the broadcast; or`
  line
  line `(d) makes any reproduction of such sound recording or visual recording where such initial`
  line `recording was done without licence or, where it was licensed, for any purpose not envisaged by such`
  line `licence; or`
  line
  line `^3[(e) sells or given on commercial rental or offer for sale or for such rental, may such sound`
  line `recording or visual recording referred to in clause (c) or clause (d).]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 12, for "RIGHTS OF BROADCASTING AUTHORITIES" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 37 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 25, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (14552)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 50
  title `Performer’s right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14552&sectionno=38&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Performer's right.-- (1) Where any performer appears or engages in any performance, he shall`
  line `have a special right to be known as the "performer's right" in relation to such performance.`
  line
  line `(2) The performer's right shall subsist until ^2[fifty years] from the beginning of the calendar year next`
  line `following the year in which the performance is made.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 14, for section 38 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by 49 of 1999, s. 4, for "twenty-five years" (w.e.f. 15-1-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 27 of 2012, s. 26 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (14553)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 51
  title `Exclusive right of performers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14553&sectionno=38A&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Exclusive right of performers.-- (1) Without prejudice to the rights conferred on authors, the`
  line `performers right which is an exclusive right subject to the provisions of this Act to do or authorise for`
  line `doing any of the following acts in respect of the performance or any substantial part thereof, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to make a sound recording or a visual recording of the performance, including--`
  line
  line `(i) reproduction of it in any material form including the storing of it in any medium by`
  line `electronic or any other means;`
  line
  line `(ii) issuance of copies of it in any material form including the storing of it in any medium by`
  line `electronic or any other means;`
  line
  line `(iii) communication of it to the public;`
  line
  line `(iv) selling or giving it on commercial rental or offer for sale or for commercial rental any`
  line `copy or the recording;`
  line
  line `(b) to broadcast or communicate the performance to the public except where the performance is`
  line `already broadcast.`
  line
  line `(2) Once a performer has, by written agreement, consented to the incorporation of his performance in`
  line `a cinematograph film he shall not, in the absence of any contract to the contrary, object to the enjoyment`
  line `by the producer of the film of the performers right in the same film:`
  line
  line `Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in this sub-section, the performer shall be entitled`
  line `for royalties in case of making of the performances for commercial use.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_b:
  sectionId (14554)
  sectionNo 38B
  orderNo 52
  title `Moral rights of the performer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 27, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14554&sectionno=38B&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[38B. Moral rights of the performer.--The performer of a performance shall, independently of his`
  line `right after assignment, either wholly or partially of his right, have the right,--`
  line
  line `(a) to claim to be identified as the performer of his performance except where omission is`
  line `dictated by the manner of the use of the performance; and`
  line
  line `(b) to restrain or claim damage in respect of any distortion, mutilation or other modification of his`
  line `performance that would be prejudicial to his reputation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this clause, it is already clarified that mere removal of any portion`
  line `of a performance for the purpose of editing, or to fit the recording within a limited duration, or any other`
  line `modification required for purely technical reasons shall not be deemed to be prejudicial to the`
  line `performer's reputation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (14555)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 53
  title `Acts not infringing broadcast reproduction right or performer’s right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 15, for section 39 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14555&sectionno=39&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[39. Acts not infringing broadcast reproduction right or performer’s right.-- No broadcast`
  line `reproduction right or performer's right shall be deemed to be infringed by--`
  line
  line `(a) the making of any sound recording or visual recording for the private use of the person`
  line `making such recording, or solely for purposes of bona fide teaching or research; or`
  line
  line `(b) the use, consistent with fair dealing, of excerpts of a performance or of a broadcast in the`
  line `reporting of current events or for bona fide review, teaching or research; or`
  line
  line `(c) such other acts, with any necessary adaptations and modifications, which do not constitute`
  line `infringement of copyright under section 52.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_a:
  sectionId (14556)
  sectionNo 39A
  orderNo 54
  title `Certain provisions to apply in case of broadcast reproduction right and performer’s.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 28, for section 39A (w.e.f. 21-6-2012)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14556&sectionno=39A&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_39_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[39A. Certain provisions to apply in case of broadcast reproduction right and performer’s rights.-- Sections 18, 19, 30, 30A, 33, 33A, 34, 35, 36, 53, 55, 58, 63, 64, 65, 65A, 65B and 66 shall,`
  line `with necessary adaptations and modifications, apply in relation to the broadcast reproduction right in any`
  line `broadcast and the performer's right in any performance as they apply in relation to copyright in a work:`
  line
  line `Provided that where copyright to performers right subsists in respect of any work or performance`
  line `that has been broadcast, no licence to reproduce such broadcast, shall be given without the consent of the`
  line `owner of rights or performer, as the case may be, or both of them:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the broadcast reproduction right or performers right shall not subsist in any`
  line `broadcast or performance if that broadcast or performance is an infringement of the copyright in any`
  line work.
  line
  line `(2) The broadcast reproduction right or the performers right shall not affect the separate copyright in`
  line `any work in respect of which, the broadcast or the performance, as the case may be, is made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (14557)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 55
  title `Power to extend copyright to foreign works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 29 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14557&sectionno=40&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by order`
  line `published in the Official Gazette, direct that all or any provisions of this Act shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to work first published in any territory outside India to which the order relates in like manner`
  line `as if they were first published within India;`
  line
  line `(b) to unpublished works, or any class thereof, the authors whereof were at the time of the making`
  line `of the work, subjects or citizens of a foreign country to which the order relates, in like manner as if`
  line `the authors were citizens of India;`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of domicile in any territory outside India to which the order relates in like manner as`
  line `if such domicile were in India;`
  line
  line `(d) to any work of which the author was at the date of the first publication thereof, or, in a case`
  line `where the author was dead at that date, was at the time of his death, a subject or citizen of a foreign`
  line `country to which the order relates in like manner as if the author was a citizen of India at that date or`
  line time;
  line
  line `and thereupon, subject to the provisions of this Chapter and of the order, this Act shall apply accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) before making an order under this section in respect of any foreign country (other than a`
  line `country with which India has entered into a treaty or which is a party to a convention relating to`
  line `copyright to which India is also a party), the Central Government shall be satisfied that that foreign`
  line `country has made, or has undertaken to make, such provisions if any, as it appears to the Central`
  line `Government expedient to require for the protection in that country of works entitled to copyright`
  line `under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) the order may provide that the provisions of this Act shall apply either generally or in relation`
  line `to such classes of works or such classes of cases as may be specified in the order;`
  line
  line `(iii) the order may provide that the term of copyright in India shall not exceed that conferred by`
  line `the law of the country to which the order relates ^1[but such a term or copyright shall not exceed the term of copyright provided under this Act];`
  line
  line `(iv) the order may provide that the enjoyment of the rights conferred by this Act shall be subject`
  line `to the accomplishment of such conditions and formalities, if any, as may be prescribed by the order;`
  line
  line `(v) in applying the provisions of this Act as to ownership of copyright, the order may make such`
  line `exception and modifications as appear necessary, having regard to the law of the foreign country;`
  line
  line `(vi) the order may provide that this Act or any part thereof shall not apply to works made before`
  line `the commencement of the order or that this Act or any part thereof shall apply to works first`
  line `published before the commencement of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_a:
  sectionId (14558)
  sectionNo 40A
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of Central Government to apply Chapter VIII to broadcasting organisations and performers in certain other countries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 49 of 1999, s. 5 (w.e.f. 15-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14558&sectionno=40A&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[40A. Power of Central Government to apply Chapter VIII to broadcasting organisations and performers in certain other countries.-- (1) If the Central Government is satisfied that a foreign`
  line `country (other than a country with which India has entered into a treaty or which is a party to a convention relating to rights of broadcasting organisations and performers to which India is also a party) has made or has undertaken to make such provisions, if any, as it appears to the Central Government`
  line `expedient to require, for the protection in that foreign country, of the rights of broadcasting organisations`
  line `and performers as is available under this Act, it may, by order published in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that the provisions of Chapter VIII shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to broadcasting organisation whose headquarters is situated in a country to which the order`
  line `relates or, the broadcast was transmitted from a transmitted situated in a country to which the order`
  line `relates as if the headquarters of such organisation were situated in India or such broadcast were made`
  line `from India;`
  line
  line `(b) to performances that took place outside India to which the order relates in like manner as if`
  line `they took place in India;`
  line
  line `(c) to performance that are incorporated in a sound recording published in a country to which the`
  line `order relates as if it were published in India;`
  line
  line `(d) to performances not fixed on a sound recording broadcast by a broadcasting organisation the`
  line `headquarters of which is located in a country to which the order relates or where the broadcast is`
  line `transmitted from a transmitted which is situated in a country to which the order relates as if the`
  line `headquarters of such organisation were situated in India or such broadcast were made from India.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) may provide that--`
  line
  line `(i) the provisions of Chapter VIII, shall apply either generally or in relation to such class or`
  line `classes of broadcasts or performances or such other class or classes of cases as may be specified in`
  line `the order;`
  line
  line `(ii) the term of the rights of broadcasting organisations and performers in India shall not exceed`
  line `such term as is conferred by the law of the country to which the order relates;`
  line
  line `(iii) the enjoyment of the rights conferred by Chapter VIII shall be subject to the accomplishment`
  line `of such conditions and formalities, if any, as may be specified in that order;`
  line
  line `(iv) Chapter VIII of any part thereof shall not apply to broadcast and performances made before`
  line `the commencement of the order or that Chapter VIII or any part thereof shall not apply to broadcasts`
  line `and performances broadcast or performed before the commencement of the order;`
  line
  line `(v) in case of ownership of rights of broadcasting organisations and performers, the provisions of`
  line `Chapter VIII shall apply with such exceptions and modifications as the Central Government may,`
  line `having regard to the law of the foreign country, consider necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (14559)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 57
  title `Provisions as to works of certain international organisations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14559&sectionno=41&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where--`
  line
  line `(a) any work is made or first published by or under the direction or control of any organisation to`
  line `which this section applies, and`
  line
  line `(b) there would, apart from this section, be no copyright in the work in India at the time of the`
  line `making or, as the case may be, of the first publication thereof, and`
  line
  line `(c) either--`
  line
  line `(i) the work is published as aforesaid in pursuance of an agreement in that behalf with the`
  line `author, being an agreement which does not reserve to the author the copyright, if any, in the`
  line `work, or`
  line
  line `(ii) under section 17 any copyright in the work would belong to the organisation;`
  line `there shall, by virtue of this section, be copyright in the work throughout India.`
  line
  line `(2) Any organisation to which this section applies which at the material time had not the legal`
  line `capacity of a body corporate shall have and be deemed at all material times to have had the legal capacity`
  line `of a body corporate for the purpose of holding, dealing with, and enforcing copyright and in connection`
  line `with all legal proceedings relating to copyright.`
  line
  line `(3) The organisations to which this section applies are such organisations as the Central Government`
  line `may, by order published in the Official Gazette, declare to be organisations of which one or more`
  line `sovereign powers or the Government or Governments thereof are members to which it is expedient that`
  line `this section shall apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (14560)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to restrict rights in works of foreign authors first published in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14560&sectionno=42&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If it appears to`
  line `the Central Government that a foreign country does not give or has not undertaken to give adequate`
  line `protection to the works of Indian authors, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that such of the provisions of this Act as confer copyright on works first published in India`
  line `shall not apply to works, published after the date specified in the order, the authors whereof are subjects`
  line `or citizens of such foreign country and are not domiciled in India, and thereupon those provisions shall`
  line `not apply to such works.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42_a:
  sectionId (14561)
  sectionNo 42A
  orderNo 59
  title `Power to restrict rights of foreign broadcasting organisations and performer’s.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14561&sectionno=42A&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[42A. Power to restrict rights of foreign broadcasting organisations and performers.-- If it`
  line `appears to the Central Government that a foreign country does not give or has not undertaken to give`
  line `adequate protection to rights of broadcasting organisations or performers, the Central Government may,`
  line `by order published in the Official Gazette, direct that such of the provisions of this Act as confer right to`
  line `broadcasting organisations or performers, as the case may be, shall not apply to broadcasting`
  line `organisations or performers whereof are based or incorporated in such foreign country or are subjects or`
  line `citizens of such foreign country and are not incorporated or domiciled in India, and thereupon those`
  line `provisions shall not apply to such broadcasting organisations or performers:]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that it does not exceed the period provided under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1999, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15-1-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 30 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (14562)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 60
  title `Orders under this Chapter to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14562&sectionno=43&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Every order made by the Central`
  line `Government under this Chapter shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before both Houses of`
  line `Parliament and shall be subject to such modifications as Parliament may make during the session in`
  line `which it is so laid or the session immediately following.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (14563)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 61
  title `Register of Copyrights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14563&sectionno=44&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `There shall be kept at the Copyright Office a register in the prescribed`
  line `form to be called the Register of Copyrights in which may be entered the names or titles of works and the`
  line `names and addresses of authors, publishers and owners of copyright and such other particulars as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (14564)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 62
  title `Entries in Register of Copyrights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14564&sectionno=45&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The author or publisher of, or the owner of or other`
  line `person interested in the copyright in, any work may make an application in the prescribed form`
  line `accompanied by the prescribed fee to the Registrar of Copyrights for entering particulars of the work in`
  line `the Register of Copyrights:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that in respect of an artistic work which is used or is capable of being used in ^2[relation to`
  line `any goods or services], the application shall include a statement to that effect and shall be accompanied`
  line `by a certificate from the Registrar of Trade Marks referred to in ^3[section 3 of the Trade Marks Act, 1999`
  line `(47 of 1999)], to the effect that no trade mark identical with or deceptively similar to such artistic work`
  line `has been registered under that Act in the name of, or that no application has been made under that Act for`
  line `such registration by, any person other than the applicant.]`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application in respect of any work under sub-section (1), the Registrar of`
  line `Copyrights may, after holding such inquiry as he may deem fit, enter the particulars of the work in the`
  line `Register of Copyrights.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso added by Act 23 of 1983, s. 16 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 31, for "relation to any goods" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "section 4 of the Trade and Merchandise Marks Act, 1958 (43 of 1958)" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (14565)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 63
  title Indexes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14565&sectionno=46&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `There shall be also kept at the Copyright Office such indexes of the Register of`
  line `Copyrights as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (14566)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 64
  title `Form and inspection of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14566&sectionno=47&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The Register of Copyrights and indexes thereof kept under`
  line `this Act shall at all reasonable times be open to inspection, and any person shall be entitled to take copies`
  line `of, or make extracts from, such register or indexes on payment of such fee and subject to such conditions`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (14567)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 65
  title `Register of Copyrights to be prima facie evidence of particulars entered therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14567&sectionno=48&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Register of Copyrights shall be prima facie evidence of the particulars entered therein and documents`
  line `purporting to be copies of any entries therein, or extracts therefrom, certified by the Registrar of`
  line `Copyrights and sealed with the seal of the Copyright Office shall be admissible in evidence in all courts`
  line `without further proof or production of the original.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (14568)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 66
  title `Correction of entries in the Register of Copyrights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14568&sectionno=49&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar of Copyrights may, in the`
  line `prescribed cases and subject to the prescribed conditions, amend or alter the Register of Copyrights by--`
  line
  line `(a) correcting any error in any name, address or particulars; or`
  line
  line `(b) correcting any other error which may have arisen therein by accidental slip or omission.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (14569)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 67
  title `Rectification of Register by High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14569&sectionno=50&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `50. Rectification of Register by ^1[High Court].--The 1[Hight Court], on application of the Registrar of Copyrights or of any person aggrieved, shall order the rectification of the Register of Copyrights by--`
  line
  line `(a) the making of any entry wrongly omitted to be made in the register, or`
  line
  line `(b) the expunging of any entry wrongly made in, or remaining on, the register, or`
  line
  line `(c) the correction of any error or defect in the register.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_a:
  sectionId (14570)
  sectionNo 50A
  orderNo 68
  title `Entries in the Register of Copyrights, etc., to be published.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 17 (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14570&sectionno=50A&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_50_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[50A. Entries in the Register of Copyrights, etc., to be published.-- Every entry made in the`
  line `Register of Copyrights or the particulars of any work entered under section 45, the correction of every`
  line `entry made in such register under section 49, and every rectification ordered under section 50, shall be`
  line `published by the Registrar of Copyrights in the Official Gazette or in such other manner as he may deem`
  line fit.]
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (14571)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 69
  title `When copyright infringed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14571&sectionno=51&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Copyright in a work shall be deemed to be infringed--`
  line
  line `(a) when any person, without a licence granted by the owner of the copyright or the Registrar of`
  line `Copyrights under this Act or in contravention of the conditions of a licence so granted or of any`
  line `condition imposed by a competent authority under this Act--`
  line
  line `(i) does anything, the exclusive right to do which is by this Act conferred upon the owner of`
  line `the copyright, or`
  line
  line `^1[(ii) permits for profit any place to be used for the communication of the work to the public`
  line `where such communication constitutes an infringement of the copyright in the work, unless he`
  line `was not aware and had no reasonable ground for believing that such communication to the public`
  line `would be an infringement of copyright; or]`
  line
  line `(b) when any person--`
  line
  line `(i) makes for sale or hire, or sells or lets for hire, or by way of trade displays or offers for`
  line `sale or hire, or`
  line
  line `(ii) distributes either for the purpose of trade or to such an extent as to affect prejudicially`
  line `the owner of the copyright, or`
  line
  line `(iii) by way of trade exhibits in public, or`
  line
  line `(iv) imports ^2*** into India,`
  line `any infringing copies of the work:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that nothing in sub-clause (iv) shall apply to the import of one copy of any work for the`
  line `private and domestic use of the importer.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the reproduction of a literary, dramatic, musical or`
  line `artistic work in the form of a cinematograph film shall be deemed to be an "infringing copy".`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 16, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. The brackets and words "(except for the private and domestic use of the importer)" omitted by Act 65 of 1984, s. 3`
  line `(w.e.f. 8-10-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 16, for the proviso (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (14572)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 70
  title `Certain acts not to be infringement of copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14572&sectionno=52&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following acts shall not constitute`
  line `an infringement of copyright, namely,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) a fair dealing with any work, not being a computer programme, for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(i) private or personal use, including research;`
  line
  line `(ii) criticism or review, whether of that work or of any other work;`
  line
  line `(iii) the reporting of current events and current affairs, including the reporting of a lecture`
  line `delivered in public;`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The storing of any work in any electronic medium for the purposes mentioned`
  line `in this clause, including the incidental storage of any computer programme which is not itself in`
  line `infringing copy for the said purposes, shall not constitute infringement of copyright.]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) the making of copies or adaptation of a computer programme by the lawful possessor of a`
  line `copy of such computer programme, from such copy--`
  line
  line `(i) in order to utilise the computer programme for the purpose for which it was supplied; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to make back-up copies purely as a temporary protection against loss, destruction or`
  line `damage in order only to utilise the computer programme for the purpose for which it was`
  line supplied;]]
  line
  line `^3[(ab) the doing of any act necessary to obtain information essential for operating interoperability`
  line `of an independently created computer programmes with other programmer by a lawful`
  line `possessor of a computer programme provided that such information is not otherwise readily`
  line available;
  line
  line `(ac) the observation, study or test of functioning of the computer programme in order to`
  line `determine the ideas and principles which underline any elements of the programme while`
  line `performing such acts necessary for the functions for which the computer programme was supplied;`
  line
  line `(ad) the making of copies or adaptation of the computer programme from a personally legally`
  line `obtained copy for non-commercial personal use;]`
  line
  line `^4[(b) the transient or incidental storage of a work or performance purely in the technical process`
  line `of electronic transmission or communication to the public;`
  line
  line `(c) transient or incidental storage of a work or performance for the purpose of providing`
  line `electronic links, access or integration, where such links, access or integration has not been expressly`
  line `prohibited by the right holder, unless the person responsible is aware or has reasonable grounds for`
  line `believing that such storage is of an infringing copy:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person responsible for the storage of the copy has received a written`
  line `complaint from the owner of copyright in the work, complaining that such transient or incidental`
  line `storage is an infringement, such person responsible for the storage shall refrain from facilitating such`
  line `access for a period of twenty-one days or till he receives an order from the competent court refraining`
  line `from facilitation access and in case no such order is received before the expiry of such period of`
  line `twenty-one days, he may continue to provide the facility of such access;`
  line
  line `(d) the reproduction of any work for the purpose of a judicial proceeding or for the purpose of a`
  line `report of a judicial proceeding;`
  line
  line `(e) the reproduction or publication of any work prepared by the Secretariat of a Legislature or,`
  line `where the legistanure consists of two Houses, by the Secretariat of either House of the Legislature,`
  line `exclusively for the use of the members of that Legislature;`
  line
  line `(f) the reproduction of any work in a certified copy made or supplied in accordance with any law`
  line `for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(g) the reading or recitation in public of reasonable extracts from a published literacy or dramatic`
  line work;
  line
  line `(h) the publication in a collection, mainly composed of non-copyright matter, bona fide intended`
  line `for instruction use, and so described in the title and in any advertisement issued by or on behalf of the`
  line `publisher, of short passages from published literary or dramatic works, not themselves published for`
  line `such use in which copyright subsists:`
  line
  line `Provided that not more than two such passages from works by the same author are published by`
  line `the same publisher during any period of five years.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- In the case of a work of joint authorship, references in this clause to passages from`
  line `works shall include references to passages from works by any one or more of the authors of those`
  line `passages or by any one or more of those authors in collaboration with any other person;`
  line
  line `(i) the reproduction of any work--`
  line
  line `(i) by a teacher or a pupil in the course of instruction; or`
  line
  line `(ii) as part of the question to be answered in an examination; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in answers to such questions;`
  line
  line `^5[(j) the performance, in the course of the activities of an educational institution, of a literary,`
  line `dramatic or musical work by the staff and students of the institution, or of a cinematograph film or a`
  line `sound recording if the audience is limited to such staff and students, the parents and guadians of the`
  line `students and persons connected with the activities of the institution or the communication to such an`
  line `audience of a cinematograph film or sound recording;]`
  line
  line `(k) the causing of a recording to be heard in public by utilising it,--`
  line
  line `(i) in an enclosed room or hall meant for the common use of residents in any residential`
  line `premises (not being a hotel or similar commercial establishment) as part of the amenities`
  line `provided exclusively or mainly for residents therein; or`
  line
  line `(ii) as part of the activities of a club or similar organisation which is not established or`
  line `conducted for profit;]`
  line
  line `(l) the performance of a literary, dramatic or musical work by an amateur, club or society, if the`
  line `performance is given to a non-paying audience, or for the benefit of a religious institution;`
  line
  line `(m) the reproduction in a newspaper, magazine or other periodical of an article on current`
  line `economic, political, social or religious topics, unless the author of such article has expressly reserved`
  line `to himself the right of such reproduction;`
  line
  line `^6[(n) the storing of a work in any medium by Electronic means by a non-commercial public`
  line `library, for preservation if the library already possesses a non-digital copy of the work;]`
  line
  line `(o) the making of not more than three copies of a book (including a pamphlet, sheet of music,`
  line `map, chart or plan) by or under the direction of the person in charge of a ^7[non-commercial public`
  line `library] for the use of the library if such book is not available for sale in India;`
  line
  line `(p) the reproduction, for the purpose of research or private study or with a view to publication, of`
  line `an unpublished literary, dramatic or musical work kept in a library, museum or other institution to`
  line `which the public has access:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the identity of the author of any such work or, in the case of a work of joint`
  line `authorship, of any of the authors is known to the library, museum or other institution, as the case may`
  line `be, the provisions of this clause shall apply only if such reproduction is made at a time more than ^8[sixty years] from the date of the death of the author or, in the case of a work of joint authorship,`
  line `from the death of the author whose identity is known or, if the identity of more authors than one is`
  line `known from the death of such of those authors who dies last;`
  line
  line `(q) the reproduction or publication of--`
  line
  line `(i) any matter which has been published in any Official Gazette except an Act of a`
  line Legislature;
  line
  line `(ii) any Act of a Legislature subject to the condition that such Act is reproduced or`
  line `published together with any commentary thereon or any other original matter;`
  line
  line `(iii) the report of any committee, commission, council, board or other like body appointed`
  line `by the Government if such report has been laid on the Table of the Legislature, unless the`
  line `reproduction or publication of such report is prohibited by the Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) any judgment or order of a court, tribunal or other judicial authority, unless the`
  line `reproduction or publication of such judgment or order is prohibited by the court, the tribunal`
  line `or other judicial authority, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(r) the production or publication of a translation in any Indian language of an Act of a`
  line `Legislature and of any rules or orders made thereunder--`
  line
  line `(i) if no translation of such Act or rules or orders in that language has been previously`
  line `been produced or published by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where a translation of such Act or rules or orders in that language has been produced`
  line `or published by the Government, if the translation is not available for sale to the public:`
  line
  line `Provided that such translation contains a statement at a prominent place to the effect that the`
  line `translation has not been authorised or accepted as authentic by the Government;`
  line
  line `^9[(s) the making or publishing of a painting, drawing, engraving or photograph of a work of`
  line `architecture or the display of a work of architecture;]`
  line
  line `(t) the making or publishing of a painting, drawing, engraving or photograph of a sculpture, or`
  line `other artistic work falling under sub-clause (iii) of clause (c) of section 2, if such work is permanently`
  line `situate in a public place or any premises to which the public has access;`
  line
  line `(u) the inclusion in a cinematograph film of--`
  line
  line `(i) any artistic work permanently situate in a public place or any premises to which the public`
  line `has access; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any other artistic work, if such inclusion is only by way of background or is otherwise`
  line `incidental to the principal matters represented in the film;`
  line
  line `(v) the use by the author of an artistic work, where the author of such work is not the owner of the`
  line `copyright therein, of any mould, cast, sketch, plan, model or study made by him for the purpose of the`
  line `work:`
  line
  line `Provided that he does not thereby repeat or imitate the main design of the work;`
  line
  line `^10[(w) the making of a three-dimensional object from a two-dimensional artistic work, such as a`
  line `technical drawing, for the purposes of industrial application of any purely functional part of a useful`
  line device;]
  line
  line `(x) the reconstruction of a building or structure in accordance with the architectural drawings or`
  line `plans by reference to which the building or structure was originally constructed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the original construction was made with the consent or licence of the owner of the`
  line `copyright in such drawings and plans;`
  line
  line `(y) in relation to a literary, ^11[dramatic, artistic or] musical work recorded or reproduced in any`
  line `cinematograph film, the exhibition of such film after the expiration of the term of copyright therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of sub-clause (ii) of clause (a), sub-clause (i) of clause (b) and`
  line `clauses (d), (f), (g), (m) and (p) shall not apply as respects any act unless that act is accompanied by`
  line `an acknowledgment`
  line
  line `(i) identifying the work by its title or other description; and`
  line
  line `(ii) unless the work is anonymous or the author of the work has previously agreed or required`
  line `that no acknowledgment of his name should be made, also identifying the author;`
  line
  line `^12[(z) the making of an ephemeral recording, by a broadcasting organisation using its own facilities`
  line `for its own broadcast by a broadcasting organisation of a work which it has the right to broadcast; and`
  line `the retention of such recording for archival purposes on the ground of its exceptional documentary`
  line character;
  line
  line `(za) the performance of a literary, dramatic or musical work or the communication to the public`
  line `of such work or of a sound recording in the course of any bona fide religious ceremony or an official`
  line `ceremony held by the Central Government or the State Government or any local authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this clause, religious ceremony includes a marriage procession`
  line `and other social festivities associated with a marriage;]`
  line
  line `^13[(zb) the adaption, reproduction, issue of copies or communication to the public of any work in`
  line `any accessible format, by--`
  line
  line `(i) any person to facilitate persons with disability to access to works including sharing with`
  line `any person with disability of such accessible format for private or personal use, educational`
  line `purpose or research; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any organisation working for the benefit of the persons with disabilities in case the normal`
  line `format prevents the enjoyment of such works by such persons:`
  line
  line `Provided that the copies of the works in such accessible format are made available to the`
  line `persons with disabilities on a non-profit basis but to recover only the cost of production:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the organisation shall ensure that the copies of works in such accessible`
  line `format as used only by persons with disabilities and takes reasonable steps to prevent its entry`
  line `into ordinary channels of business.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this sub-clause, "any organisation" includes and organisation`
  line `registered under section 12A of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and working for the benefit of`
  line `persons with disability or reorgnised under Chapter X of the Persons with Disabilities (Equal`
  line `Opportunities, Protection or Rights and full Participation) Act, 1995 (1 of 1996) or receiving grants`
  line `from the government for facilitationg access to persons with disabilities or an educational institution`
  line `or library or archives recognised by the Government;`
  line
  line `(zc) the importation of copies of any literary or artistic work, such as labels, company logos or`
  line `promotional or explanatory material, that is purely incidental to other goods or products being`
  line lawfully.]
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply to the doing of any act in relation to the translation of`
  line `a literary, dramatic or musical work or the adaptation of a literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work as`
  line `they apply in relation to the work itself.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 32, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 17 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 of 1999, s. 7 (w.e.f. 15-1-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 32, for clauses (b), (c), (d), (e), (f), (g), (h), (i) and (j) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 17, for clauses (j) and (k) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 32, for clause (n) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for "public library" (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 49 of 1999, s. 7, for "fifty years" (w.e.f. 15-1-2000).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 17, for clause (s) (w.e.f. 9-8-1995).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 32, for clause (w) (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for dramatic or (w.e.f. 21-6-2012)`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 17 (w.e.f. 9-8-1995).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 32 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a:
  sectionId (14573)
  sectionNo 52A
  orderNo 71
  title `Particulars to be included in records and video Films.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14573&sectionno=52A&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[52A. Particulars to be included in records and video Films.-- (1) No person shall publish`
  line a
  line `^2[sound recording] in respect of any work unless the following particulars are displayed on the ^2[sound`
  line `recording] and on any container thereof, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the name and address of the person who has made the record;`
  line
  line `(b) the name and address of the owner of the copyright in such work; and`
  line
  line `(c) the year of its first publication.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall publish a video film in respect of any work unless the following particulars are`
  line `displayed in the video film, when exhibited, and on the video cassette or other container thereof,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if such work is a cinematograph film required to be certified for exhibition under the`
  line `provisions of the Cinematograph Act, 1952 (37 of 1952), a copy of the certificate granted by the`
  line `Board of Film Certification under section 5A of that Act in respect of such work;`
  line
  line `(b) the name and address of the person who has made the video film and a declaration by him that`
  line `he has obtained the necessary licence or consent from the owner of the copyright, in such work for`
  line `making such video film; and`
  line
  line `(c) the name and address of the owner for the copyright in such work.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for "record" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_b:
  sectionId (14574)
  sectionNo 52B
  orderNo 72
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Accounts and audit.] Omitted by the Copyright Act, 2012 (27 of 2012), s. 33 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_b_footnotes
