obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (14575)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 73
  title `Importation of infringing copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 34, for section 53 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14575&sectionno=53&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `^1[53. Importation of infringing copies.-- (1) The owner of any right conferred by this act in respect`
  line `of any work or any performance embodied in such work, or his duly authorised agent, may give notice in`
  line `writing to be Commissioner of Customs, or to any other officer authorised in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Board of Excise and Customs, --`
  line
  line `(a) that he is the owner of the said right, with proof thereof, and`
  line
  line `(b) that he requests the Commissioner for a period specified in the notice, which shall not exceed`
  line `one year, to treat infringing copies of the work as prohibited goods, and that infringing copies of the`
  line `work are expected to arrive in India at a time and a place specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner, after scrutiny of the evidence furnished by the owner of the right and on being`
  line `satisfied may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), treat infringing copies of the work as prohibited`
  line `goods that have been imported into India, excluding goods in transit:`
  line
  line `Provided that owner of the work deposits such amount as the Commissioner may require as security`
  line `having regard to the likely expenses on demurrage, cost of storage and compensation to the importer in`
  line `case it is found that works are not infringing copies.`
  line
  line `(3) When any goods treated as prohibited under sub-section (2) have been detained, the Customs`
  line `Officer detaining them shall inform the importer as well as the person who gave notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) of the such goods within forty-eight hours of their detention.`
  line
  line `(4) The Customs Officer shall release the goods, and they shall not longer be treated as prohibited`
  line `goods, if the person who gave notice under sub-section (1) does not produce any order from a court`
  line `having jurisdiction as to the temporary or permanent disposal of such goods within fourteen days from the`
  line `date of their detention.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_a:
  sectionId (14576)
  sectionNo 53A
  orderNo 74
  title `Resale share right in original copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14576&sectionno=53A&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[53A. Resale share right in original copies.(1) In the case of resale for a price exceeding ten`
  line `thousand rupees, of the original copy of a painting, sculpture or drawing, or of the original manuscript of`
  line `a literary or dramatic work or musical work, the author of such work if he was the first owner of rights`
  line `under section 17 or his legal heirs shall, notwithstanding any assignment of copyright in such work, have`
  line `a right to share in the resale price of such original copy or manuscript in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that such right shall cease to exist on the expiration of the term of copyright in the work.`
  line
  line `(2) The share referred to in sub-section (1) shall be such as the ^2[Commercial Court] may fix 3***:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^2[Commercial Court] may fix different shares for different classes of work:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in no case shall the share exceed ten percent, of the resale price.`
  line
  line `(3) If any dispute arises regarding the right conferred by this section, it shall be referred to the`
  line `^2[Commercial Court] whose decision shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 18 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for "Appellate Board" (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  line
  line `3.The words "and the decision of the Appellate Board in this behalf shall be final" omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (14577)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 75
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s.10, for “Appellate Board” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14577&sectionno=54&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, the`
  line `expression owner of copyright shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) an exclusive licensee;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an anonymous or pseudonymous literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work, the`
  line `publisher of the work, until the identity of the author or, in the case of an anonymous work of joint`
  line `authorship, or a work of joint authorship published under names all of which are pseudonyms, the`
  line `identity of any of the authors, is disclosed publicly by the author and the publisher or is otherwise`
  line `establishment to the satisfaction of the ^1[Comnercial Court] by that author or his legal representatives.`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (14578)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 76
  title `Civil remedies for infringement of copyright.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14578&sectionno=55&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where copyright in any work has been`
  line `infringed, the owner of the copyright shall, except as otherwise provided by this Act, be entitled to all`
  line `such remedies by way of injunction, damages, accounts and otherwise as are or may be conferred by law`
  line `for the infringement of a right:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the defendant proves that at the date of the infringement he was not aware and had no`
  line `reasonable ground for believing that copyright subsisted in the work, the plaintiff shall not be entitled to`
  line `any remedy other than an injunction in respect of the infringement and a decree for the whole or part of`
  line `the profits made by the defendant by the sale of the infringing copies as the court may in the`
  line `circumstances deem reasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in the case of a literary, dramatic, musical or artistic work, ^1[or, subject to the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 13, a cinematograph film or sound recording, a name purporting to be that of`
  line `the author, or the publisher, as the case may be, of that work, appears] on copies of the work as published,`
  line `or, in the case of an artistic work, appeared on the work when it was made, the person whose name so`
  line `appears or appeared shall, in any proceeding in respect of infringement of copyright in such work, be`
  line `presumed, unless the contrary is proved, to be the author or the publisher of the work, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) The costs of all parties in any proceedings in respect of the infringement of copyright shall be in`
  line `the discretion of the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 35, for "a name purporting to be that of the author or the publisher, as the case may be, appear"`
  line `(w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (14579)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 77
  title `Protection of separate rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14579&sectionno=56&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, where the several rights`
  line `comprising the copyright in any work are owned by different persons, the owner of any such right shall,`
  line `to the extent of that right, be entitled to the remedies provided by this Act and may individually enforce`
  line `such right by means of any suit, action or other proceeding without making the owner of any other right a`
  line `party to such suit, action or proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (14580)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 78
  title `Author’s special rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14580&sectionno=57&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Independently of the authors copyright and even after the`
  line `assignment either wholly or partially of the said copyright, the author of a work shall have the right--`
  line
  line `(a) to claim authorship of the work; and`
  line
  line `((b) to restrain or claim damages in respect of any distortion, mutilation, modification or other act`
  line `in relation to the said work ^2*** if such distortion, mutilation, modification or other act would be`
  line `prejudicial to his honour or reputation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the author shall not have any right to restrain or claim damages in respect of any`
  line `adaptation of a computer programme to which clause (aa) of sub-section (1) of section 52 applies.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Failure to display a work or to display it to the satisfaction of the author shall not be`
  line `deemed to be an infringement of the rights conferred by this section.]`
  line
  line `(2) The right conferred upon an author of a work by sub-section (1), ^3***, may be exercised by the`
  line `legal representatives of the author.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 20, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995)`
  line
  line `2. The words "which is done before the expiration of the term of copyright" omitted by Act 27 0f 2012, s. 36 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012)`
  line
  line `3. The words "other than the right to claim authorship of the work" omitted by Act 27 of 2012, s. 36 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (14581)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 79
  title `Rights of owner against persons possessing or dealing with infringing copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14581&sectionno=58&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `All infringing`
  line `copies of any work in which copyright subsists, and all plates used or intended to be used for the`
  line `production of such infringing copies, shall be deemed to be the property of the owner of the copyright,`
  line `who accordingly may take proceedings for the recovery of possession thereof or in respect of the`
  line `conversion thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that the owner of the copyright shall not be entitled to any remedy in respect of the`
  line `conversion of any infringing copies, if the opponent proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that he was not aware and had no reasonable ground to believe that copyright subsisted in the`
  line `work of which such copies are alleged to be infringing copies; or`
  line
  line `(b) that he had reasonable grounds for believing that such copies or plates do not involve`
  line `infringement of the copyright in any work.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (14582)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 80
  title `Restriction on remedies in the case of works of architecture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 21, for "the Specific Relief Act, 1877 (1 of 1877)" (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14582&sectionno=59&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in ^1[the Specific Relief Act, 1963 (47 of 1963)], where the construction of a building or other`
  line `structure which infringes or which, if completed, would infringe the copyright in some other work has`
  line `been commenced, the owner of the copyright shall not be entitled to obtain an injunction to restrain the`
  line `construction of such building or structure or to order its demolition.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in Section 58 shall apply in respect of the construction of a building or other structure`
  line `which infringes or which, if completed, would infringe the copyright in some other work.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (14583)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 81
  title `Remedy in the case of groundless threat of legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for " in section 42 the Specific Relief Act, 1877 (1 of 1977)" (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14583&sectionno=60&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Where any person claiming to`
  line `be the owner of copyright in any work, by circulars, advertisements or otherwise, threatens any other`
  line `person with any legal proceedings or liability in respect of an alleged infringement of the copyright any`
  line `person aggrieved thereby may, notwithstanding anything contained ^1[in section 34 of the Specific Relief`
  line `Act, 1963 (47 of 1963)], institute a declaratory suit that the alleged infringement to which the threats`
  line `related was not in fact an infringement of any legal rights of the person making such threats and may in`
  line `any such suit--`
  line
  line `(a) obtain an injunction against the continuance of such threats; and`
  line
  line `(b) recover such damages, if any, as he has sustained by reason of such threats:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section does not apply if the person making such threats, with due diligence,`
  line `commences and prosecutes an action for infringement of the copyright claimed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (14584)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 82
  title `Owner of copyright to be party to the proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14584&sectionno=61&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every civil suit or other proceeding`
  line `regarding infringement of copyright instituted by an exclusive licensee, the owner of the copyright shall,`
  line `unless the court otherwise directs, be made a defendant and where such owner is made a defendant, he`
  line `shall have the right to dispute the claim of the exclusive licensee.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any civil suit or other proceeding regarding infringement of copyright instituted by an`
  line `exclusive licensee is successful, no fresh suit or other proceeding in respect of the same cause of action`
  line `shall lie at the instance of the owner of the copyright.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (14585)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 83
  title `Jurisdiction of court over matters arising under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14585&sectionno=62&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every suit or other civil`
  line `proceeding arising under this Chapter in respect of the infringement of copyright in any work or the`
  line `infringement of any other right conferred by this Act shall be instituted in the district court having`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of sub-section (1), a "district court having jurisdiction" shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or any other law for the time being`
  line `in force, include a district court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction, at the time of the institution`
  line `of the suit or other proceeding, the person instituting the suit or other proceeding or, where there are more`
  line `than one such persons, any of them actually and voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally`
  line `works for gain.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (14586)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 84
  title `Offences of infringement of copyright or other rights conferred by this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14586&sectionno=63&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `who knowingly infringes or abets the infringement of--`
  line
  line `(a) the copyright in a work, or`
  line
  line `(b) any other right conferred by this Act ^1[except the right conferred by section 53A],`
  line
  line `^2[shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which`
  line `may extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which`
  line `may extend to two lakh rupees:]`
  line
  line `Provided that ^1[where the infringement has not been made for gain in the course of trade or business]`
  line `the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment, impose a sentence of`
  line `imprisonment for a term of less than six months or a fine of less than fifty thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Construction of a building or other structure which infringes or which, if completed,`
  line `would infringe the copyright in some other work shall not be an offence under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 21 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 5, for "shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with`
  line `both" (w.e.f. 8-10-1984)`
obj_root_law_sections_63_a:
  sectionId (14587)
  sectionNo 63A
  orderNo 85
  title `Enhanced penalty on second and subsequent convictions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14587&sectionno=63A&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_63_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[63A. Enhanced penalty on second and subsequent convictions.-- Whoever having already been`
  line `convicted of an offence under section 63 is again convicted of any such offence shall be punishable for`
  line `the second and for every subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `one year but which may extend to three years and with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees`
  line `but which may extend to two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^2[where the infringement has not been made for gain in the course of trade or business] the court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment, impose a sentence of`
  line `imprisonment for a term of less than one year or a fine of less than one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purposes of this section, no cognizance shall be taken of any conviction`
  line `made before the commencement of the Copyright (Amendment) Act, 1984 (65 of 1984).]`
obj_root_law_sections_63_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 6 (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 22 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995)`
obj_root_law_sections_63_b:
  sectionId (14588)
  sectionNo 63B
  orderNo 86
  title `Knowing use of infringing copy of computer programme to be an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14588&sectionno=63B&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_63_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[63B. Knowing use of infringing copy of computer programme to be an offence.-- Any person`
  line `who knowingly makes use on a computer of an infringing copy of a computer programme shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than seven days but which may extend to`
  line `three years and with fine which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to two`
  line `lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the computer programme has not been used for gain or in the course of trade or`
  line `business, the Court may, for adequate and special reasons to be mentioned in the judgment, not impose`
  line `any sentence of imprisonment and may impose a fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (14589)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power of police to seize infringing copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14589&sectionno=64&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Any police officer, not below the rank of a`
  line `sub-inspector, may, if he is satisfied that an offence under section 63 in respect of the infringement of`
  line `copyright in any work has been, is being, or is likely to be, committed, seize without warrant, all copies of the work, and all the plates used for the purposes of making infringing copies of the work, wherever`
  line `found, and all copies and plates so seized shall, as soon as practicable be produced before a Magistrate.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any person having an interest in any copies of a work ^2[, or plates] seized under sub-section (1)`
  line `may, within fifteen days of such seizure, make an application to the Magistrate for such copies ^2[, or plates] being restored to him and the Magistrate, after hearing the applicant and the complainant and`
  line `making such further inquiry as may be necessary, shall make such order on the application as he may`
  line `deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 7, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (14590)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 88
  title `Possession of plates for purpose of making infringing copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "one year, or with fine, or with both" (w.e.f. 8-10-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14590&sectionno=65&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Any person who knowingly`
  line `makes, or has in his possession, any plate for the purpose of making infringing copies of any work in`
  line `which copyright subsists shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to ^1[two years and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_65_a:
  sectionId (14591)
  sectionNo 65A
  orderNo 89
  title `Protection of technological measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_a_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 37 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14591&sectionno=65A&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_65_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [65A. Protection of technological measures.-- (1) Any person who circumvents an effective`
  line `technological measures applied for the purpose of protecting any of the rights conferred by this Act, with`
  line `the intention of infringing such rights, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to two`
  line `years and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall prevent any person from,--`
  line
  line `(a) doing anything referred to therein for a purpose not expressly prohibited by this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person facilitating circumvention by another person of a technological measure`
  line `for such a purpose shall maintain a complete record of such other person including his name, address`
  line `and all relevant particulars necessary to identify him and the purpose for which he has been`
  line `facilitated; or`
  line
  line `(b) doing anything necessary to conduct encryption research using a lawfully obtained encrypted`
  line `copy; or`
  line
  line `(c) conducting any lawful investigation; or`
  line
  line `(d) doing anything necessary for the purpose of testing the security of a computer system or a`
  line `computer network with the authorisation of its owner; or`
  line
  line `(e) operator; or`
  line
  line `(f) doing anything necessary to circumvent technological measures intended for identification or`
  line `surveillance of a user; or`
  line
  line `(g) taking measures necessary in the interest of national security.]`
obj_root_law_sections_65_b:
  sectionId (14592)
  sectionNo 65B
  orderNo 90
  title `Protection of Rights Management Information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 37 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14592&sectionno=65B&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_65_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[65B. Protection of Rights Management Information.-- Any person, who knowingly, --`
  line
  line `(i) removes or alters any rights management information without authority, or`
  line
  line `(ii) distributes, imports for distribution, broadcasts or communicates to the public, without`
  line `authority, copies of any work, or performance knowing that electronic rights management`
  line `information has been removed or altered without authority,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to two years and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the rights management information has been tampered with in any work, the owner of`
  line `copyright in such work may also avail of civil remedies provided under Chapter XII against the persons`
  line `indulging in such acts.]`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (14593)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 91
  title `Disposal of infringing copies or plates for purpose of making infringing copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14593&sectionno=66&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `The Court`
  line `trying any offence under this Act may, whether the alleged offender is convicted or not, order that all`
  line `copies of the work or all plates in the possession of the alleged offender, which appear to it to be`
  line `infringing copies, or plates for the purpose of making infringing copies, be delivered up to the owner of`
  line `the copyright ^1[or may make such order as it may deem fit regarding the disposal of such copies of`
  line plates.]
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (14594)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 92
  title `Penalty for making false entries in register, etc., for producing or tendering false entries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14594&sectionno=67&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) makes or causes to be made a false entry in the Register of Copyrights kept under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) makes or causes to be made a writing falsely purporting to be a copy of any entry in such`
  line `register, or`
  line
  line `(c) produces or tenders or causes to be produced or tendered as evidence any such entry or`
  line `writing, knowing the same to be false,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (14595)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 93
  title `Penalty for making false statements for the purpose of deceiving or influencing any authority or officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14595&sectionno=68&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `[Penalty for making false statements for the purpose of deceiving or influencing any`
  line `authority or officer.] Omitted by the Jan Vishwas (Amendment of Provision) Act, 2023 (18 of 2023), s. 2`
  line `and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68_a:
  sectionId (14596)
  sectionNo 68A
  orderNo 94
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 52A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14596&sectionno=68A&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[68A. Penalty for contravention of section 52A.-- Any person who publishes a ^2[sound recording] or a video film in contravention of the provisions of section 52A shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to three years and shall also be liable to fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 65 of 1984, s. 9 (w.e.f. 8-10-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 2, for "record" (w.e.f. 10-5-1995)`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (14597)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 95
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14597&sectionno=69&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to the company for, the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of such offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any person liable to any punishment,`
  line `if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence`
  line `to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence was committed with the consent or connivance`
  line `of, or is attributable to any negligence on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of`
  line `the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of persons; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (14598)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 96
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 22, for "a presidency magistrate or a magistrate of the first class" (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14598&sectionno=70&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `No Court inferior to that of ^1[a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class] shall try any offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (14599)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 97
  title `Appeals against certain orders of Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14599&sectionno=71&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order made under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 64 or section 66 may, within thirty days of the date of such order appeal to the`
  line `Court to which appeals from the court making the order ordinarily lie, and such appellate court may direct`
  line `that execution of the order be stayed pending disposal of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (14600)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 98
  title `Appeals against orders of Registrar of Copyrights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 10, for section 72 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14600&sectionno=72&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `^1[72. Appeals against orders of Registrar of Copyrights.--(1) Any person aggrieved by any final`
  line `decision or order of the Registrar of Copyrights may, within three months from the date of the order or`
  line `decision, appeal to the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such appeal shall be heard by a single Judge of the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such Judge may, if he so thinks fit, refer the appeal at any stage of the proceeding`
  line `to a Bench of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an appeal is heard by a single Judge, a further appeal shall lie to a Bench of the High Court`
  line `within three months from the date of decision or order of the single Judge.`
  line
  line `(4) In calculating the period of three months provided for an appeal under this section, the time taken`
  line `in granting a certified copy of the order or record of the decision appealed against shall be excluded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (14601)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 99
  title `Procedure for appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14601&sectionno=73&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may make rules consistent with this Act as to the`
  line `procedure to be followed in respect of appeals made to it under section 72.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (14602)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 100
  title `Registrar of Copyrights and Appellate Board to possess certain powers of civil courts`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14602&sectionno=74&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `74. Registrar of Copyrights and ^1[Appellate Board] to possess certain powers of civil courts.--The Registrar of Copyrights ^2*** shall have the powers of a civil court when trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely, --`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of enforcing the attendance of witnesses, the local limits of the jurisdiction of the Registrar of Copyrights or the ^1[Appellate Board], as the case may be, shall be the limits of the territory of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.160, for Copyright Board (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. The words “and the Appellate Board” omitted by Act 33 of 2021, s. 10 (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (14603)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 101
  title `Orders for payment of money passed by Registrar of Copyrights and Appellate Board to be executable as a decree`
  content `75. Orders for payment of money passed by Registrar of Copyrights and ^1[Appellate Board] to be executable as a decree.--Every order made by the Registrar of Copyrights or the ^1[Appellate Board] under this Act for the payment of any money or by the High Court in any appeal against any such order of the ^1[Appellate Board] shall, on a certificate issued by the Registrar of Copyrights, the ^1[Appellate Board] or the Registrar of the High Court, as the case may be, be deemed to be a decree of a civil court and shall be executable in the same manner as a decree of such court.`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.160, for "Copyright Board" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14603&sectionno=75&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (14604)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 102
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14604&sectionno=76&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any`
  line `person in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (14605)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 103
  title `Certain persons to be public servants.`
  content `Every officer appointed under this Act ^1*** shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  footnotes `1. The words "and every member of the Appellate Board" omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14605&sectionno=77&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (14606)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 104
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14606&sectionno=78&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the Central Government`
  line `may make rules to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[* * * * *];`
  line
  line `(b) the form of complaints and applications to be made, and the licences to be granted, under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(c) the procedure to be followed in connection with any proceeding before the Registrar of`
  line Copyrights;
  line
  line `^2[(cA) the form and manner in which an organisation may apply to the ^3[Appellate Board] for`
  line `compulsory licence for disabled and the fee which may accompany such application under`
  line `sub-section 31B;`
  line
  line `(cB) the manner in which a person making sound recording may give prior notice of his intention`
  line `to make sound recording under sub-section (2) of section 31C;`
  line
  line `(cC) the register and books of account and the details of existing stock which a person making`
  line `sound recording may maintain under sub-section (5) of section 31C;`
  line
  line `(cD) the manner in which prior notice may be given by a broadcasting organisation under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 31D;`
  line
  line `(cE) the reports and accounts which may be maintained under clause (a), and the inspection of`
  line `records and books of account which may be made under clause (b) or sub-section (7) of section 31D];`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) the conditions for submission of application under sub-section (2) of section 33;`
  line `(cb) the conditions subject to which a copyright society may be registered under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 33;`
  line
  line `(cc) the inquiry for cancellation of registration under sub-section (4) of section 33;`
  line
  line `^5[(ccA) the manner in which a copyright society may publish its Tariff Scheme under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 33A;`
  line
  line `(ccB) the fee which is to be paid before filing an appeal to the 3`
  line `[Appellate Board] under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 33A;`
  line
  line `(ccC) the form of application for renewal of registration of a copyright society and the fee which`
  line `may accompany such application under sub-section (3A) of section 33;]`
  line
  line `(cd) the conditions subject to which the copyright society may accept authorisation under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 34 and the conditions subject to which owners or rights have`
  line `right to withdraw such authorisation under clause (d) of that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(ce) the conditions subject to which a copyright society may issue licences, collect fees and`
  line `distribute such fees amongst owners of rights under sub-section (3) of section 34;]`
  line
  line `(cf) the manner in which the approval of the owners of rights regarding collection and distribution`
  line `of fees, approval for utilisation of any amount collected as fees and to provide to such owners`
  line `information concerning activities in relation to the administration of their rights under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 35;`
  line
  line `(cg) the returns to be filed by copyright societies to the Registrar of Copyrights under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 36;]`
  line
  line `(d) the manners of determining any royalties payable under this Act, and the security to be taken`
  line `for the payment of such royalties;`
  line
  line `^5[(da) the manner of payment of royalty under clause (j) of sub-section (1) of section 52;`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *]`
  line
  line `(e) the form of Register of Copyrights to be kept under this Act and the particulars to be entered`
  line therein;
  line
  line `(f) the matters in respect of which the Registrar of Copyrights and the ^3[ Appellate Board] shall`
  line `have powers of a civil court;`
  line
  line `(g) the fees which may be payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) the regulation of business of the Copyright Office and of all things by this Act placed under`
  line `the direction or control of the Registrar of Copyrights.`
  line
  line `^7[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 160 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 2012, s. 39 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.160, for Copyright Board (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 24 (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 38 of 1994, s. 24, for sub-clause (da) (w.e.f. 10-5-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Omitted by Act 27 of 2012, s. 38 (w.e.f. 21-6-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 1983, s. 23, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 9-8-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (14607)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 105
  title `Repeals, savings and transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.160, for "Copyright Board" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712&sectionId=14607&sectionno=79&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00006_195714_1517807321712
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Indian Copyright Act, 1914 (3 of 1914),`
  line `and the Copyright Act of 1911 passed by the Parliament of the United Kingdom as modified in its`
  line `application to India by the Indian Copyright Act, 1914 ( 3 of 1914), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person has, before the commencement of this Act, taken any action whereby he has`
  line `incurred any expenditure or liabilities in connection with the reproduction or performance of any work in`
  line `a manner which at the time was lawful or for the purpose of or with a view to the reproduction or`
  line `performance of a work at a time when such reproduction or performance would, but for the coming into`
  line `force of this Act, have been lawful, nothing in this section shall diminish or prejudice any rights or`
  line `interests arising from or in connection with such action which are subsisting and valuable at the said date,`
  line `unless the person who, by virtue of this Act, becomes entitled to restrain such reproduction or`
  line `performance, agrees to pay such compensation as, failing agreement, may be determined by the`
  line `^1[Appellate Board].`
  line
  line `(3) Copyright shall not subsist by virtue of this Act in any work in which copyright did not subsist`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act under any Act repealed by sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Where copyright subsisted in any work immediately before the commencement of this Act, the`
  line `rights comprising such copyright shall, as from the date of such commencement, be the rights specified in`
  line `section 14 in relation to the class of works to which such work belongs, and where any new rights are`
  line `conferred by that section, the owner of such rights shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case where copyright in the work was wholly assigned before the commencement of`
  line `this Act, the assignee or his successor-in-interest;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the person who was the first owner of the copyright in the work under any`
  line `Act repealed by sub-section (1) or his legal representatives.`
  line
  line `(5) Except as otherwise provided in this Act, where any person is entitled immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act to copyright in any work or any right in such copyright or to an interest in any`
  line `such right, he shall continue to be entitled to such right or interest for the period for which he would have`
  line `been entitled thereto if this Act has not come into force.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing contained in this Act shall be deemed to render any act done before its commencement an`
  line `infringement of copyright if that act would not otherwise have constituted such an infringement.`
  line
  line `(7) Save as otherwise provided in this section, nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the`
  line `application of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with respect to the effect of repeals.`
